itors in the Ghanaian Pavilion:\n* 2019 \u2014 [[El Anatsui]], [[Ibrahim Mahama (artist)|Ibrahim Mahama]], [[Felicia Abban]], [[Lynette Yiadom-Boakye]], [[John Akomfrah]], [[Selasi Awusi Sosu]] (Curator: [[Nana Oforiatta Ayim]]<ref name=\"auto1\"/>)\n\nGrenada'''<big>Bold text</big><big>Big text</big>''\nin 2017, Grenada participated'in the Venice Biennale at an exclusive space in Zattere, Dorsoduro, all allocated for the exhibition entitled The Bridge, where international artists from nations with sea outlets explored the collective idea of \"own identity\". \nCurator: Omar Donia; participating artists:  Alexandre Murucci, Khaled Hafez, Jason de Caires Taylor, Asher Mains, Milton Williams, Rashid Al Kahlifa, Zena Assi and Mahmoud Obaidi.\n\n\n===Hong Kong===\nList of exhibitors in the Hong Kong Pavilion:\n* 2009 \u2014 Pak Sheung Chuen (Curator: Tobias Berger)\n* 2011 \u2014 [[Kwok Mang Ho]] (known as Frog King) \n* 2013 \u2014 [[Lee Kit]] (Curators: [[Lars Nittve]], Yung Ma)\n* 2015 \u2014 Tsang Kin-wah (Curators: Doryun Chong, Stella Fong)<ref>Julia Halperin (July 16, 2014), [http://theartnewspaper.com/articles/Tsang-Kinwah-to-represent-Hong-Kong-at-next-Venice-Biennale-/33298 Tsang Kin-wah to represent Hong Kong at next Venice Biennale] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141026114523/http://www.theartnewspaper.com/articles/Tsang-Kinwah-to-represent-Hong-Kong-at-next-Venice-Biennale-/33298 |date=2014-10-26 }} ''[[The Art Newspaper]]''.</ref>\n* 2017 \u2014 Samson Young\n* 2019 \u2014 [[Shirley Tse]] (Curator: Christina Li)<ref>Shirley Nwangwa (June 18, 2018), [http://www.artnews.com/2018/06/18/shirley-tse-stage-installation-hong-kong-organized-collateral-event-2019-venice-biennale/ Shirley Tse Will Rep Hong Kong at 2019 Venice Biennale] ''[[ARTnews]]''.</ref>\n\n===Holy See===\n* 2013 \u2014 Studio Azzurro, Lawrence Carroll, Josef Koudelka\n* 2015 \u2014 [[Monika Bravo]], Elpida Hadzi-Vasileva, M\u00e1rio Macilau (Curator: Micol Forti)\n\n===Iceland===\nIn 1984, as Finland had joined Norway and Sweden in the Nordic Pavilion, Iceland was given the opportunity to rent the Finnish pavilion until 2006.<ref name=\"Martino\"/> The [[Center for Icelandic Art|Icelandic Art Center]] commissions the Icelandic Pavilion at the Venice Biennale.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://icelandicartcenter.is/about-us/the-center/|title=Role and Goals|work=Icelandic Art Center}}</ref>\n\nList of exhibitors in the Icelandish Pavilion:<ref>[http://www.artnews.is/issue012/012_venhist.htm A Brief Look Back: Icelandic Participation at the Venice Biennale] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120328015335/http://www.artnews.is/issue012/012_venhist.htm |date=2012-03-28 }}, LIST Icelandic Art News, 28 February 2007.</ref>\n* 1960 \u2014 [[J\u00f3hannes Sveinsson Kjarval]], [[\u00c1smundur Sveinsson]]\n* 1972 \u2014 [[Svavar Gu\u00f0nason]], [[\u00deorvaldur Sk\u00falason]] \n* 1980 \u2014 Magn\u00fas P\u00e1lsson\n* 1982 \u2014 [[Gunnar \u00c1rnason]], [[Kristj\u00e1n Gu\u00f0mundsson]]\n* 1984 \u2014 Kristj\u00e1n Davidsson\n* 1986 \u2014 [[Err\u00f3]]\n* 1988 \u2014 Gunnar \u00d6rn\n* 1990 \u2014 Helgi \u00deorgils Fri\u00f0j\u00f3nsson\n* 1995 \u2014 Birgir Andr\u00e9sson\n* 1997 \u2014 [[Steina and Woody Vasulka|Steina Vasulka]]<ref name=\"auto2\">[[Roberta Smith]] (June 16, 1997), [https://www.nytimes.com/1997/06/16/arts/another-venice-biennale-shuffles-to-life.html Another Venice Biennale Shuffles to Life] ''[[New York Times]]''.</ref>\n* 1999 \u2014 Sigur\u00f0ur \u00c1rni Sigur\u00f0sson\n* 2001 \u2014 Finnbogi P\u00e9tursson\n* 2003 \u2014 R\u00far\u00ed\n* 2005 \u2014 [[Gabr\u00edela Fri\u00f0riksd\u00f3ttir]]\n* 2007 \u2014 Steingr\u00edmur Eyfj\u00f6r\u00f0 (Curator: Hanna Styrmisd\u00f3ttir)\n* 2009 \u2014 [[Ragnar Kjartansson (performance artist)|Ragnar Kjartansson]] (Curators: Mark\u00fas Th\u00f3r Andr\u00e9sson, Doroth\u00e9e Kirch)\n* 2011 \u2014 Libia Castro & \u00d3lafur \u00d3lafsson (Curator: Ellen Blumenstein)\n* 2013 \u2014 [[Katr\u00edn Sigurdard\u00f3ttir|Katr\u00edn Sigur\u00f0ard\u00f3ttir]] (Curators: Mary Ceruti, Ilaria Bonacossa)\n* 2015 \u2014 [[Christoph B\u00fcchel]] (Curator: N\u00edna Magn\u00fasd\u00f3ttir)\n* 2017 \u2014 Egill S\u00e6bj\u00f6rnsson (Curator: Stefanie B\u00f6ttcher)\n\n===India===\nIn 2011, India was represented for the first time after 116 years, with the support of the culture ministry and the organizational participation of the Lalit Kala Akademi.<ref name=\"artinfo\">{{cite web |url=http://www.artinfo.com/news/story/33767/artinfos-comprehensive-guide-to-the-2011-venice-biennale-national-pavilions/ |title=ARTINFO's Comprehensive Guide to the 2011 Venice Biennale National Pavilions |work=ARTINFO |publisher=Louise Blouin Media |date=May 30, 2011 |accessdate=October 22, 2011}}</ref> Biennale organizers had reportedly invited the country in past years, but the government had declined, a decision attributed to a lack of communication between the culture ministry and the country's [[National Gallery of Modern Art]].<ref name=\"artinfo\"/>\n* 2011 \u2014 Mriganka Madhukaliya, Sonal Jain, Zarina Hashmi, Gigi Scaria, Praneet Soi (Curator: [[Ranjit Hoskote]])\n* 2015 \u2014 [[Shilpa Gupta]], [[Rashid Rana]] (Exhibition jointly held with [[Pakistan]])\n* 2019 \u2014 [[Nandalal Bose]], [[Atul Dodiya]], [[Rummana Hussain]], GR Iranna, [[Jitish Kallat]], [[Shakuntala Kulkarni]], [[Ashim Purkayastha]]<ref>Kabir Jhala and Anna Brady (March 22, 2019), [https://www.theartnewspaper.com/news/india-announces-venice-biennale-artist-line-up-for-gandhi-themed-exhibition India announces artist line-up of Gandhi-themed exhibition at Venice Biennale] ''[[The Art Newspaper]]''.\n</ref>\n\n===Iran===\n* 1958 - [[Monir Shahroudy Farmanfarmaian]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.vogue.com/article/cosmic-geometry-the-life-and-work-of-monir-shahroudy-farmanfarmaian|title=Cosmic Geometry: The Life and Work of Monir Shahroudy Farmanfarmaian|website=Vogue|accessdate=June 3, 2019}}</ref>\n* 2003 - [[Behrouz Daresh]], [[Hossein KhoroJerdi]], and [[Ahmad Nadalian]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://kayhanlife.com/culture/art/iran-venice-biennale-visit-iranian-pavilion/|title=Iran at the Venice Biennial (Part I) &#124; KAYHAN LIFE|first=Kayhan|last=Life|accessdate=June 3, 2019}}</ref>\n* 2017 - [[Bizhan Bassiri]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://kayhanlife.com/culture/art/iran-at-the-venice-biennale-a-visit-to-the-iranian-pavilion/|title=Iran at the Venice Biennale: A Visit to the Iranian Pavilion &#124; KAYHAN LIFE|first=Natasha|last=Phillips|accessdate=June 3, 2019}}</ref>\n* 2019 - [[Samira Alikhanza]], [[Ali Mir-Azimi]], and [[Reza  Lavasani]]  <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://ifpnews.com/exclusive/irans-pavilion-opens-in-venice-biennial-arte-2019/|title=Iran\u2019s Pavilion Opens in Venice Biennial Arte 2019|first=IFP Editorial|last=Staff|date=May 11, 2019|website=IFP News - Iran Front Page|accessdate=June 3, 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Iraq===\nIn 2011, Iraq returned to the Biennale for the first time after a 35-year absence. The title of the Iraq Pavilion was \"Acqua Ferita\" (translated as \"Wounded Water\"). Six Iraqi artists from two generations interpreted the theme of water in their works, which made up the exhibition. \n* 2011 \u2014 Adel Abidin, Halim Al Karim, Ahmed Alsoudani, Ali Assaf, Azad Nanakeli, Walid Siti\n* 2013 \u2014 'Welcome to Iraq', curated by [[Jonathan Watkins]], commissioned by [[Ruya Foundation]]. Artists: Abdul Raheem Yassir (b. 1951), Akeel Khreef (b. 1979), Ali Samiaa (b. 1980), Bassim Al-Shaker (b. 1986), Cheeman Ismaeel (b. 1966), Furat al Jamil (b. 1965), Hareth Alhomaam (b. 1987), Jamal Penjweny (b. 1981), Kadhim Nwir (b. 1967), Yaseen Wami (b. 1973), Hashim Taeeh.<ref>Ruya Foundation, ''Announcement'', March 21, 2013 [https://ruyafoundation.org/en/2013/03/announcement-of-artists-names/]</ref>\n* 2015 \u2014 'Invisible Beauty', curated by Philippe Van Cauteren, commissioned by [[Ruya Foundation]]. Artists:  [[Latif_al-Ani|Latif Al Ani]], Akam Shex Hadi, Rabab Ghazoul, Salam Atta Sabri and Haider Jabbar.<ref>Ruya Foundation, Invisible Beauty the Iraq Pavilion at the 56th Venice Biennale, April 1, 2016 [https://ruyafoundation.org/en/project/invisible-beauty-2/]</ref>\n* 2017 \u2014 'Archaic', curated by Tamara Chalabi and Paolo Colombo, commissioned by [[Ruya Foundation]]. Artists: Sherko Abbas, [[Sadik Kwaish Alfraji]], [[Francis Al\u00ffs]], Ali Arkady, Luary Fadhil, [[Shakir Hassan Al Said]], Nadine Hattom, [[Jawad Saleem]], Sakar Sleman<ref>Chalabi, T., ''Archaic: The Pavilion of Iraq : 57th International Art Exhibition La Biennale Di Venezia'', Mousse Publishing, 2017</ref><ref>Ruya Foundation, ''Archaic the Iraq Pavilion at the 57th Venice Biennale'', March 10, 2017 [https://ruyafoundation.org/en/project/venice-biennale-2017/]</ref>\n* 2019 \u2014 'Fatherland: Serwan Baran', curated by Tamara Chalabi and Paolo Colombo, commissioned by [[Ruya Foundation]]. Artist: Serwan Baran (b. 1968). <ref>Alex Greenberger (February 22, 2019), [http://www.artnews.com/2019/02/22/serwan-baran-will-represent-iraq-2019-venice-biennale/ Serwan Baran Will Represent Iraq at the 2019 Venice Biennale] ''[[ARTnews]]''.</ref><ref>Ruya Foundation, ''Fatherland: Serwan Baran the Iraq Pavilion at the 58th Venice Biennale'', April 1, 2019 [https://ruyafoundation.org/en/project/fatherland/]</ref>\n\n===Ireland===\nList of exhibitors in the Irish Pavilion:\n* 1950 \u2014 [[Norah McGuinness]], [[Nano Reid]]\n* 1956 \u2014 [[Louis le Brocquy]], Hilary Heron\n* 1960 \u2014 Patrick Scott\n* 1993 \u2014 Dorothy Cross, Willie Doherty\n* 1995 \u2014 [[Kathy Prendergast]]<ref>[[Michael Kimmelman]] (July 9, 1995), [https://www.nytimes.com/1995/07/09/arts/art-view-venice-biennale-startling-songs-of-the-body.html Venice Biennale: Startling Songs Of the Body...] ''[[New York Times]]''.</ref>\n* 1997 \u2014 [[Jaki Irvine]], Alastair MacLennan<ref name=\"auto2\"/>\n* 1999 \u2014 Anne Tallentire\n* 2001 \u2014 Siobhan Hapaska, Grace Weir\