g_spider_man_2}}\n\n{{Portal bar|Speculative fiction|Film|United States|Comics}}\n{{Spider-Man in popular media}}\n{{Spider-Man films}}\n{{Marvel Comics films}}\n{{Marc Webb}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{Good article}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Amazing Spider-Man 2014}}\n[[Category:2014 films]]\n[[Category:2014 3D films]]\n[[Category:2010s science fiction action films]]\n[[Category:2010s sequel films]]\n[[Category:2010s superhero films]]\n[[Category:American films]]\n[[Category:American 3D films]]\n[[Category:American science fiction action films]]\n[[Category:American sequel films]]\n[[Category:Biopunk films]]\n[[Category:Columbia Pictures films]]\n[[Category:Fictional portrayals of the New York City Police Department]]\n[[Category:Films scored by Mike Einziger]]\n[[Category:Films scored by Junkie XL]]\n[[Category:Films scored by Johnny Marr]]\n[[Category:Films scored by Pharrell Williams]]\n[[Category:Films scored by Hans Zimmer]]\n[[Category:Films about genetic engineering]]\n[[Category:American films about revenge]]\n[[Category:Films directed by Marc Webb]]\n[[Category:Films produced by Avi Arad]]\n[[Category:Films produced by Matt Tolmach]]\n[[Category:Films set in New York City]]\n[[Category:Films set on airplanes]]\n[[Category:Films shot in New York (state)]]\n[[Category:Films shot in New York City]]\n[[Category:Films set in 2014]]\n[[Category:Motion capture in film]]\n[[Category:IMAX films]]\n[[Category:Films with screenplays by Alex Kurtzman and Roberto Orci]]\n[[Category:Spider-Man films]]\n[[Category:The Amazing Spider-Man (2012 film series)]]\n[[Category:Films adapted into video games]]\n[[Category:Teen superhero films]]\n", "text_old": "{{other uses}}\n{{short description|2014 superhero film directed by Marc Webb}}\n{{use mdy dates|date=May 2014}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = The Amazing Spider-Man 2\n| image          = The Amazing Spiderman 2 poster.jpg \n| alt            = Spider-Man upside down on the side of the OsCorp tower with the film's title, credits and release date below.\n| caption        = Theatrical release poster\n| director       = [[Marc Webb]]\n| producer       = {{Plain list|\n* [[Avi Arad]]\n* [[Matt Tolmach]]\n}}\n| screenplay     = {{Plain list |\n* [[Alex Kurtzman]]\n* [[Roberto Orci]]\n* [[Jeff Pinkner]]\n}}\n| story          = {{Plain list |\n* Alex Kurtzman\n* Roberto Orci\n* Jeff Pinkner\n* [[James Vanderbilt]]\n}}\n| based on       = {{Based on|[[The Amazing Spider-Man]]|[[Stan Lee]]|[[Steve Ditko]]}}\n| starring       = {{Plain list |\n* [[Andrew Garfield]]\n* [[Emma Stone]]\n* [[Jamie Foxx]]\n* [[Dane DeHaan]]\n* [[Campbell Scott]]\n* [[Embeth Davidtz]]\n* [[Colm Feore]]\n* [[Paul Giamatti]]\n* [[Sally Field]]\n<!--- Per poster billing block --->\n}}\n| music          = {{Plain list |\n* [[Hans Zimmer]]\n* The Magnificent Six{{efn|The one-time supergroup includes [[Pharrell Williams]], [[Johnny Marr]], [[Mike Einziger]], [[Junkie XL]], Steve Mazzaro, and Andrew Kawczynski.}}\n}}\n| cinematography = [[Dan Mindel]]\n| editing        = [[Pietro Scalia]]\n| studio         = {{Plain list |\n* [[Columbia Pictures]]\n* [[Marvel Entertainment]]\n* Arad Productions, Inc.\n* Matt Tolmach Productions}}\n| distributor    = [[Sony Pictures Motion Picture Group#Sony Pictures Releasing|Sony Pictures Releasing]]\n| released       = {{Film date|2014|4|18|[[Mexico]]|ref1=<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.upi.com/News_Photos/Entertainment/The-Amazing-Spider-Man-2-in-Tokyo/8282/|title=\"The Amazing Spider-Man 2\" in Tokyo|publisher=[[United Press International]]|work=UPI desk|date=March 31, 2014|archivedate=March 30, 2014|archiveurl=http://www.upi.com/search?ss=%22The+Amazing+Spider-Man+2%22+in+Tokyo+|accessdate=November 24, 2015}}</ref>|2014|5|2|United States}}\n| runtime        = 142 minutes<!--Theatrical runtime: 142:25--><ref>{{cite web|title=''The Amazing Spider-Man 2'' [2D] (12A)|url= http://www.bbfc.co.uk/releases/amazing-spider-man-2-film-0 |publisher=[[British Board of Film Classification]]|accessdate=April 5, 2014}}</ref>\n| country        = United States <!-- Per Template:Infobox film, the parameter is for \"the home country or countries of the film's main production companies.\" -->\n| language       = English\n| budget         = <!-- DO NOT ALTER THE BUDGET. THE SOURCE PROVIDES TWO DIFFERENT FIGURES FOR IT -->$200\u2013293 million<ref>{{Cite journal|last=FilmL.A.|title=2014 Feature Film Study|url=https://www.filmla.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/2014_FeatureFilm_study_v10_WEB.pdf#page=7|journal=FilmL.A. Feature Film Study|date=May 2015|accessdate=November 11, 2017}}</ref>\n| gross          = $709 million<ref name=\"mojo\">{{cite web|url=http://www.boxofficemojo.com/movies/?id=amazingspiderman2.htm|title=The Amazing Spider-Man 2 (2014)|website=[[Box Office Mojo]]|accessdate=April 23, 2016}}</ref>\n}}\n'''''The Amazing Spider-Man 2''''' (internationally titled '''''The Amazing Spider-Man 2: Rise of Electro''''')<ref>{{cite news |last=Baillie |first=Russell |url=http://www.nzherald.co.nz/entertainment/news/article.cfm?c_id=1501119&objectid=11242795 |title=Movie review: The Amazing Spider-Man 2: Rise of Electro |newspaper=[[The New Zealand Herald]] |date=April 24, 2014 |archive-date=May 5, 2014 |archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/6PLoA5YMr?url=http://www.nzherald.co.nz/entertainment/news/article.cfm?c_id=1501119&objectid=11242795 |url-status=live }}</ref> is a 2014 American [[superhero film]] featuring the [[Marvel Comics]] character [[Spider-Man]]. The film was directed by [[Marc Webb]] and produced by [[Avi Arad]] and [[Matt Tolmach]]. It is the [[Spider-Man in film|fifth theatrical ''Spider-Man'' film]] produced by [[Columbia Pictures]] and [[Marvel Entertainment]], the sequel to 2012's ''[[The Amazing Spider-Man (2012 film)|The Amazing Spider-Man]]'' and the second and final film in ''The Amazing Spider-Man'' duology. The studio hired [[James Vanderbilt]] to write the screenplay and [[Alex Kurtzman]] and [[Roberto Orci]] to rewrite it.<ref name=\"TAS sequel\">{{cite web|last=Kit |first=Borys |last2=Fernandez |first2=Jay A |title=James Vanderbilt returning to pen sequel |url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/james-vanderbilt-returning-pen-spider-171190 |work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |date=March 24, 2011 |accessdate=March 24, 2011 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/619oUBpKW?url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/james-vanderbilt-returning-pen-spider-171190 |archivedate=August 23, 2011 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.deadline.com/2012/04/alex-kurtzman-roberto-orci-writing-sequel-to-amazing-spider-man/ | title = Alex Kurtzman & Roberto Orci Re-Writing Sequel To 'Amazing Spider-Man' | website=Deadline Hollywood | date= April 24, 2012 | accessdate=April 24, 2012 | last=Fleming | first=Mike | archivedate=October 17, 2013 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20131017180406/http://www.deadline.com/2012/04/alex-kurtzman-roberto-orci-writing-sequel-to-amazing-spider-man/ | url-status=live}}</ref> The film stars [[Andrew Garfield]] as Peter Parker / Spider-Man, alongside [[Emma Stone]], [[Jamie Foxx]], [[Dane DeHaan]], [[Campbell Scott]], [[Embeth Davidtz]], [[Colm Feore]], [[Paul Giamatti]], and [[Sally Field]].\n\nWhen New York is put under siege by Oscorp, it is up to Spider-Man to save the city he swore to protect as well as his loved ones.\n\nDevelopment of ''The Amazing Spider-Man 2'' began after the success of ''The Amazing Spider-Man''. DeHaan, Giamatti, Jones, and Cooper were cast between December 2012 and February 2013. Filming took place in [[New York City]] from February to June 2013. The film was released in 2D, [[3D film|3D]], and [[IMAX|IMAX 3D]] on May 2, 2014, in the United States with two international premieres being held between March 31 and April 10 of that year. It received mixed reviews from critics and audiences and grossed $709 million worldwide, making it the [[2014 in film#Highest-grossing films|ninth-highest-grossing film of 2014]], but the second-lowest-grossing Spider-Man film to date.\n\n''The Amazing Spider-Man 2'' was originally envisioned as the beginning of a shared fictional universe, which would have continued with two sequels and several spin-offs, most notably films centered on [[Venom (Marvel Comics character)|Venom]] and the [[Sinister Six]]. Due to performing below expectations, all subsequent installments were cancelled and a [[Reboot (fiction)|new iteration]] of the character, portrayed by [[Tom Holland (actor)|Tom Holland]] in the [[Marvel Cinematic Universe]] (MCU), began with the 2016 film ''[[Captain America: Civil War]]''. The planned spin-offs were re-purposed for a [[Sony's Marvel Universe|timeline separate from ''The Amazing Spider-Man'' continuity and the MCU]], beginning with 2018's [[Venom (2018 film)|''Venom'']], the upcoming 2020's ''[[Morbius (film)|Morbius]]'' & ''[[Venom 2]]''.\n\n==Plot==\n<!-- Per WP:FILMPLOT, the plot summary should be 400-700 words. -->\n[[Oscorp]] scientist Richard Parker records a video message to explain his disappearance. Later, he and his wife, Mary, are aboard a private jet hijacked by an assassin sent to kill Richard and his wife. Richard and Mary fight off the man, but the ensuing struggle causes the plane to crash, killing both Richard and Mary, after he uploads the video.\n\nIn the present time, Richard's son, Peter, continues to fight crime as [[Spider-Man]]. He pursues and apprehends [[Rhino (comics)|Aleksei Sytsevich]]. Later, Peter meets with his girlfriend [[Gwen Stacy]] at their high school graduation ceremony and, insisting he keep his vow to her late father, ends their relationship. Peter's childhood friend, [[Harry Osborn]], returns to Manhattan to see his terminally-ill father, [[Norman Osborn|Norman]], CEO of Oscorp. Norman explains his illness is genetic, and Harry is at the age where it first develops. Norman gives Harry a small device he claims contains his life's work. The next day, Norman dies, and Harry is appointed the new Oscorp CEO.\n\nWhile working in an Oscorp laboratory, electrical engineer [[Electro (Marvel Comics)|Max Dillon]] shocks himself by accident and falls into a tank of genetically-engineered [[electric eel]]s. They attack him, and he mutates into a living electric generator. Meanwhile, Peter attempts to maintain a friendship with Gwen, but she reveals that she may move to England if she earns a scholarship to [[Oxford University]]. Before they can discuss it, Dillon wanders into [[Times Square]], accidentally causing a blackout, and is stopped by Spider-Man after a battle. Dillon is taken to the Ravencroft Institute, where he is studied by German scientist [[Dr. Kafka]]. Meanwhile, the first symptoms of Harry's illness are showing, and he uses the device Norman gave him to deduce that Spider-Man's blood could help save him. He asks Peter, who has been selling photos of Spider-Man to the ''[[Daily Bugle]]'', to aid him in finding Spider-Man. Peter refuses, unsure of what effects the transfusion would have. Although he later comes to Harry as Spider-Man, he still refuses, and Harry becomes resentful towards Spider-Man. Oscorp vice-president Donald Menken frames Harry for covering up Dillon's accident, removes him as CEO and takes control of Oscorp. Harry's assistant, [[Felicia Hardy]], informs him of equipment that could help him, so he makes a deal with Dillon, who now calls himself \"Electro,\" to get him back inside the Oscorp building. There he finds a suit of armor and other equipment made by Norman, as well as venom from the now-destroyed genetically-altered spiders. The venom accelerates Harry's illness, and transforms him into a [[Green Goblin|goblin-like creature]], but the suit's built-in emergency protocol restores his health and cures his disease.\n\nPeter uses information left by his father to locate the video message in an abandoned subway station's hidden lab. Richard explains that he had to leave because he refused to cooperate with Norman's plans to make biogenetic weapons. Peter then hears a voicemail from Gwen, telling him that she was offered the Oxford scholarship, and is heading to the airport earlier than expected. He catches her and professes his love for her, and they agree to go to England together. Electro causes another blackout, and Peter heads off to battle him as Spider-Man. Gwen follows, and together, they restore power, and [[overcurrent|overload]] Electro's body, killing him.\n\nThe transformed Harry, who now calls himself \"Green Goblin\", arrives equipped with Norman's armor and weaponry. Upon seeing Gwen, he deduces Spider-Man's secret identity and, swearing revenge for being refused the blood transfusion, kidnaps her and takes her to the top of a clock tower. Spider-Man defeats Harry, but his webbing breaks during the battle, and Gwen falls. Peter tries but is unable to save her. Mourning her death,  the depressed Peter ends his career as Spider-Man.\n\nFive months later, Harry is coping with the aftereffects of his transformation while incarcerated at Ravencroft. His associate, [[The Gentleman (comics)|Gustav Fiers]], visits Harry and the pair discuss forming their own [[Sinister Six|team]]. Harry orders Fiers to start with Sytsevich. Later, an unknown team of men break Sytsevich out of prison. Equipped with an electromechanical suit of armor, Sytsevich calls himself the Rhino and rampages through the streets. Peter, inspired by Gwen's graduation speech, resumes his role as Spider-Man, and confronts him.\n<!--PLEASE DO NOT ADD ABOUT THE X-MEN MID CREDIT SCENE. IT IS NOT PART OF THE FILM, AS NOTED IN THE \"POST-PRODUCTION\" SECTION. THANK YOU.-->\n\n==Cast==\n{{further|List of Spider-Man films cast members|List of Spider-Man supporting characters}}\n{{multiple image\n | direction = vertical\n | width     = 175\n | footer    = Andrew Garfield (top) and Emma Stone (bottom), the principal cast of the film.\n | image1    = Andrew Garfield by Gage Skidmore (cropped).jpg\n | alt1      = \n | caption1  = \n | image2    = Emma Stone by Gage Skidmore.jpg\n | alt2      = \n | caption2  = \n}}\n\n* [[Andrew Garfield]] as [[Spider-Man|Peter Parker / Spider-Man]]: <br />An orphaned teenage boy who received spider-powers after being bitten by a genetically altered spider. Peter first uses his powers to try to hunt down the [[Burglar (comics)|killer]] of his uncle in ''[[The Amazing Spider-Man (2012 film)|The Amazing Spider-Man]]'' but soon decides to use his powers to fight crime as the vigilante known as Spider-Man. Garfield explained that the suit that he would wear in the film would undergo a new design. Garfield hoped to bring back the theme of him being an orphan stating, \"I wanna keep exploring that theme of being fatherless, being motherless, searching for purpose and finding a purpose within himself\". He felt that it was his responsibility to take on the role and that he does not take it lightly.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.eonline.com/news/362945/amazing-spider-man-2-andrew-garfield-talks-redesigned-costume-exploring-spidey-s-double-life | title=Amazing Spider-Man 2: Andrew Garfield Talks Redesigned Costume, Exploring Spidey's \"Double Life\" | publisher=[[E!]] | date=November 13, 2012 | accessdate=April 3, 2013 | author=Loinaz, Alexis}}</ref>\n**[[Max Charles]] as young Peter Parker.\n* [[Emma Stone]] as [[Gwen Stacy]]: <br />A high school student and Peter's love interest. When asked about Peter and Gwen's relationship in the sequel, Stone said, \"She saves him more than he saves her. She's incredibly helpful to Spider-Man&nbsp;... He's the muscle, she's the brains.\"<ref name=emmastoney>{{cite web|url=http://www.totalfilm.com/news/emma-stone-talks-saving-spidey-in-the-amazing-spider-man-2 |title=Emma Stone talks saving Spidey in The Amazing Spider-Man 2 |work=[[Total Film]] |date=January 4, 2013 |accessdate=January 4, 2013 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140701013428/http://www.totalfilm.com/news/emma-stone-talks-saving-spidey-in-the-amazing-spider-man-2 |archivedate=July 1, 2014 }}</ref>\n* [[Jamie Foxx]] as [[Electro (Marvel Comics)|Max Dillon / Electro]]: <br />An [[electrical engineer]] who works for Oscorp Industries and later transforms into a powerful, electrical creature following an accident, then taking the alias of \"Electro\". Foxx described the character as \"a nobody\" who initially idolizes Spider-Man.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/1699031/amazing-spider-man-2-villian-electro/|title=Exclusive: 'Spider-Man' Villain Jamie Foxx Reveals Major Origin Details | publisher= [[MTV News]] | first=Josh | last= Wigler | date= December 17, 2012 | accessdate=May 3, 2014 | archivedate= May 3, 2014 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20140503060101/http://www.mtv.com/news/1699031/amazing-spider-man-2-villian-electro/ | url-status=live}}</ref> He develops an obsession with Spider-Man after being saved by him and obtains his powers through an accident at Oscorp involving [[electric eel]]s. Foxx revealed that the character would be redesigned to be more grounded, and that the villain's classic yellow and green suit would be omitted in favor of a modern look, as depicted in the film.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.movieweb.com/news/the-amazing-spider-man-2-electro-costume-is-getting-a-modern-redesign |title=The Amazing Spider-Man 2 Electro Costume Is Getting a Modern Redesign |publisher=Movieweb.com|date=2012-12-17}}</ref>\n* [[Dane DeHaan]] as [[Harry Osborn]] / [[Green Goblin]]: <br />Peter's longtime friend for 10 years and son of Norman Osborn. He was sent away to boarding school around the same time Peter's parents disappeared, and meets him for the first time.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mtv.com/videos/interview/938674/dane-dehaan-talks-jamie-foxx-the-amazing-spider-man-2-bromance.jhtml|title=Dane DeHaan Talks Jamie Foxx 'The Amazing Spider-Man 2' Bromance|publisher=MTV|date=July 19, 2013}}</ref> He eventually assumes the role of the Green Goblin after injecting a special serum of spider-venom into his body, initially injected to provide a cure, which instead turns him into a hideous, psychotic, goblin-like creature. As the Green Goblin, Harry dons a technological suit capable of healing him and can fly with the use of a large glider.\n* [[Campbell Scott]] as [[Richard and Mary Parker|Richard Parker]]: Peter's father.\n* [[Embeth Davidtz]] as [[Richard and Mary Parker|Mary Parker]]: Peter's mother.\n* [[Colm Feore]] as [[Donald Menken]]: <br />Oscorp's Vice President and Head of the Board. He is often in dispute with Harry over his capabilities of being a CEO to Oscorp, claiming that because Harry is a boy, he is incapable of leading the company.\n* [[Paul Giamatti]] as [[Rhino (comics)|Aleksei Sytsevich / Rhino]]: <br />A Russian hired killer for the [[Russian Mafia]], who allies with Harry and receives a massive, well-armored, robotic, rhino-like suit from him, deciding to call himself \"the Rhino\". Giamatti said of his character, \"He's a Russian mobster. Russians are always good villains. I have an ability to just destroy things\", he said. \"My accent is pretty hammy. I loved doing it. It seemed to me like an opportunity to be as over-the-top hammy as possible. It was really fun.\"<ref name=toronto-rhino>{{cite news|url=http://www.torontosun.com/2013/09/06/paul-giamatti-thrilled-to-play-rhino-in-the-amazing-spider-man-2 |title=Paul Giamatti thrilled to play Rhino in 'The Amazing Spider-Man 2' |first=Liz |last=Braun |agency=[[QMI Agency]] |work=[[Toronto Sun]] |date=September 6, 2013 |accessdate=May 3, 2014 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6PHoMwkGF?url=http://www.torontosun.com/2013/09/06/paul-giamatti-thrilled-to-play-rhino-in-the-amazing-spider-man-2 |archivedate=May 3, 2014 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n* [[Sally Field]] as [[Aunt May|May Parker]]: Peter's aunt. Field was critical of the lack of depth in her role; during a 2016 appearance on ''[[The Howard Stern Show]]'', she said that \"It's really hard to find a three-dimensional character in [the film], and you work it as much as you can, but you can't put 10 pounds of shit in a five-pound bag.\"<ref>{{cite news|last1=Delbyck|first1=Cole|title=Sally Field Compares Her 'Spider-Man' Role To A Bag Of S**t|url=https://www.huffingtonpost.com/entry/sally-field-spider-man-aunt-may_us_56e84ab8e4b0860f99da8c5a|accessdate=January 27, 2018|work=[[HuffPost]]|date=March 15, 2016}}</ref>\n\n[[Felicity Jones]] portrays Felicia, Norman's assistant at Oscorp, and later Harry's. While Jones was only credited as Felicia in the final film, her surname was revealed as \"Hardy\" in a marketing video for the film releasing on digital HD formats, in reference to [[Black Cat (Marvel Comics)|Black Cat]]'s alter ego Felicia Hardy.<ref>{{cite av media|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=9EvXCHB2Smk|title=The Amazing Spider-Man 2: Now on Digital HD!|author=Sony Pictures Entertainment|publisher=YouTube|date=August 6, 2014|accessdate=August 20, 2014|time=0:07}}</ref> [[Marton Csokas]] portrays [[Ashley Kafka]], the head of [[Ravencroft|Ravencroft Institute]], and [[B. J. Novak]] appears as [[Alistair Smythe]], Dillon's boss and an Oscorp employee. Kari Coleman, Charlie DePew, [[Skyler Gisondo]], and Jacob Rodier reprise their roles from [[The Amazing Spider-Man (2012 film)|the first film]] as [[Helen Stacy]], Philip Stacy, Howard Stacy, and Simon Stacy, respectively, with the latter being uncredited. [[Chris Cooper]], who portrays [[Norman Osborn]], the founder of Oscorp and Harry Osborn's father, and [[Denis Leary]], who reprises his role as [[George Stacy]], appearing as a ghost in Peter's visions, are also in uncredited roles. Spider-Man co-creator, [[Stan Lee]], has a cameo appearance as a guest at Peter and Gwen's graduation ceremony. [[Michael Massee]] reprises his role as the \"Man in the Shadows\" from the first film, with the character now credited as \"[[Gentleman (character)|Gustav Fiers (The Gentleman)]]\". [[Aidy Bryant]] appears as a woman dressed as the Statue of Liberty. [[J.D. Walsh (actor)|J.D. Walsh]] appears as an online instructor demonstrating how batteries work.\n\n==Production==\n\n===Development===\n{{quote box|\n| align = right\n| width = 30em\n| quote = The ''Spider-Man'' film franchise is one of our studio's greatest assets. We are thrilled with the creative team we have assembled to delve more deeply into the world that Marc, Avi and Matt have begun to explore in ''The Amazing Spider-Man'' and ''The Amazing Spider-Man 2''. We believe that Marc, Alex, and Drew have uniquely exciting visions for how to expand the ''Spider-Man'' universe in each of these upcoming films.\n| source = \u2014Sony<ref name=\"Spider-Man universe\">{{cite web|url=http://www.deadline.com/2013/11/sony-pictures-plans-spider-man-sequels-and-spinoffs/|title=Update: Sony Pictures Plans More Spider-Man Sequels And Spinoffs \u2013 But Still No Marvel Reunion|publisher =[[Deadline Hollywood]]|last=Lieberman|first=David|date=November 21, 2013|accessdate=November 21, 2013}}</ref>}}\n\nThe sequel's villain was teased in the 2012 film.<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.cinemablend.com/new/Video-Spider-Man-Director-Marc-Webb-Talks-Hints-Future-Villains-Lizard-Look-30019.html | title= Video: Spider-Man Director Marc Webb Hints at Future Villains and the Lizard's Look | publisher =Cinema Blend | date=March 17, 2012 | accessdate=April 4, 2012 | last = Eisenberg | first = Eric}}</ref> Webb stated that the origin story would further unfold in the second installment.<ref name=\"orgin\">{{cite web | url=http://splashpage.mtv.com/2012/04/10/amazing-spider-man-origin/ | title =Untold 'Spider-Man' Origin Will Unfold Over 'A Few Movies,' Director Says | publisher=MTV | date= April 10, 2012 | accessdate = April 11, 2012 | last =Wigler | first = Josh}}</ref> In June 2012, Webb said he was unsure whether he would return,<ref>{{cite web | url= http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2012/06/26/marc-webb-the-amazing-spider-man_n_1626287.html | title= Marc Webb, 'Amazing Spider-Man' Director, On The Specter of Sam Raimi | publisher =Huffington Post | date= June 26, 2012 | accessdate = June 26, 2012 | last= Ryan | first= Mike}}</ref> though it was confirmed on September 28, 2012, that he would return to direct the sequel.<ref name=\"Garfield & Webb return\">{{cite web|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2012/09/28/andrew-garfield-marc-webb-amazing-spider-man-2_n_1924327.html |title=Andrew Garfield & Marc Webb Return For 'Amazing Spider-Man 2' |publisher=Huffington Post |date=September 28, 2012 |accessdate=September 28, 2012}}</ref><ref name=\"Garfield & Webb return 2\">{{cite web|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/amazing-spider-man-sequel-returns-375025 |title=Andrew Garfield and Director Marc Webb to Return for 'Amazing Spider-Man' Sequel |last=Siegel |first=Tatiana |work=The Hollywood Reporter |date=September 28, 2012 |accessdate=September 28, 2012}}</ref> He stated that he \"wanted to create a universe that not only can withstand but anticipate future storylines\" while also \"working in and of itself for one movie.\"<ref>{{cite web | url=http://collider.com/amazing-spider-man-sequel/177106/ | title='The Amazing Spider-Man' Director Marc Webb Talks Sequels and His Original Villain Creation: The Mime; Plus, Two New Posters | publisher=Collider.com | date=July 2, 2012 | accessdate=July 3, 2012 | last=Trumbore |first= Dave}}</ref> Andrew Garfield had also expressed hope to reprise his role,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/andrew-garfield-hopes-star-spider-342498 |title=Andrew Garfield Hopes to Star in 'Spider-Man' Sequel |work=The Hollywood Reporter |date=June 27, 2012 |accessdate=July 19, 2012 |last=Carlson |first=Erin}}</ref> and in September 2012, it was confirmed that he would do so.<ref name=\"Garfield & Webb return\"/><ref name=\"Garfield & Webb return 2\"/> Emma Stone was later confirmed to be reprising her role as Gwen Stacy, having signed a contract for two ''Amazing Spider-Man'' sequels.<ref name=emmastoney/><ref>{{cite web|last=Moore|first=Ben|url=http://screenrant.com/emma-stone-spider-man-reboot-gwen-stacy-deat-benm-93520/|title=Emma Stone Talks Spider-Man Reboot & Death of Gwen Stacy|publisher=Screen Rant|accessdate=January 2, 2011|date=December 22, 2010}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.superherohype.com/news/articles/108309-confirmed-emma-stone-to-play-gwen-stacy-in-spider-man|title=Confirmed! Emma Stone to Play Gwen Stacy in Spider-Man!|work=[[Superhero Hype!]]|publisher=CraveOnline|date=October 5, 2010|accessdate=October 5, 2010}}</ref> The original costume and mask from ''The Amazing Spider-Man'' was altered and has lens in the mask, making the eyes bigger. The web shooters were also modified.<ref>{{cite web|last=Schaefer|first=Sandy|title='Amazing Spider-Man 2' Mask Reveal; Dane DeHeaan Bulking Up for Harry Osborn|url=http://screenrant.com/amazing-spider-man-2-costume-dane-dehaan-harry-osborn/|publisher=Screenrant.com|accessdate=February 25, 2013}}</ref>\n\nActor [[J. K. Simmons]] expressed interest in reprising his role as [[J. Jonah Jameson]] from [[Sam Raimi]]'s ''Spider-Man'' trilogy should the studio offer it to him.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.craveonline.com/film/articles/193147-jk-simmons-is-open-to-playing-j-jonah-jameson-in-amazing-spider-man-2 |title=J.K. Simmons is Open to Playing J. Jonah Jameson in Amazing Spider-Man 2 |publisher=CraveOnline.com |last=Topel |first=Fred |date=July 30, 2012 |accessdate=May 3, 2014 | archivedate= April 22, 2014 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20140422010122/http://www.craveonline.com/film/articles/193147-jk-simmons-is-open-to-playing-j-jonah-jameson-in-amazing-spider-man-2 | url-status =live}}</ref> In October 2012, [[Electro (Marvel Comics)|Electro]] was rumored as the next villain.<ref>{{cite web|last=Sneider |first=Jeff |url=https://variety.com/2012/film/news/shailene-woodley-in-talks-for-spider-man-2-exclusive-1118060562/ |title = Shailene Woodley in talks for 'Spider-Man 2' |work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] | accessdate=October 11, 2012|date=October 10, 2012 }}</ref> [[Jamie Foxx]] was given the role.<ref>{{cite web |last= Kroll |first= Justin|url= https://variety.com/2012/film/news/jamie-foxx-in-talks-to-play-spider-man-2-villain-1118061562/|title= Jamie Foxx in talks to play 'Spider-Man 2' villain |work=Variety |date=October 1, 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url =http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/michael-bay-testing-hot-young-390516 |title=Michael Bay Testing Hot Young Actors for 'Transformers 4' Leads (Exclusive) |work=The Hollywood Reporter |date = November 16, 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web| url = http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/spider-man-2-actors-testing-393106 |title='Spider-Man 2' Testing Quartet of Actors for Harry Osborn Role |work = The Hollywood Reporter |date= November 19, 2012}}</ref> That December, Foxx confirmed that he was cast as the character, and during an interview with MTV, explained that the redesign of the character would be more grounded as well as details of his depiction, which were based upon the [[Ultimate Marvel]] incarnation of Electro.<ref>{{cite web |last= Wigler |first= Josh| url= http://www.mtv.com/news/articles/1699031/amazing-spider-man-2-villian-electro.jhtml | title = Exclusive: 'Spider-Man' Villain Jamie Foxx Reveals Major Origin Details | publisher = MTV | date = December 17, 2012}}</ref> On December 3, 2012, Marc Webb revealed that [[Dane DeHaan]] was chosen to play Harry Osborn.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/dane-dehaan-cast-as-harry-396834 |title=Dane DeHaan to Play Harry Osborn in 'Spider-Man' Sequel |work=The Hollywood Reporter |date=December 3, 2012 |first=Borys |last=Kit |accessdate=May 30, 2014}}</ref> [[Paul Giamatti]] was confirmed as a cast member in February 2013.<ref>Nealey, Joshua (February 3, 2013). [http://www.hypable.com/2013/02/05/the-amazing-spider-man-2-synopsis-revealed-paul-giamatti-and-colm-feore-join-cast/ \"'The Amazing Spider-Man 2' synopsis revealed, Paul Giamatti and Colm Feore officially join cast\"]. Hypable.</ref> [[Felicity Jones]] confirmed her involvement with the film under an undisclosed role.<ref name=the-rhino>{{cite web|last=Kit |first=Boris |url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/paul-giamatti-talks-play-rhino-415899 |title=Paul Giamatti in Talks to Play The Rhino in 'Spider-Man 2' (Exclusive)|work=The Hollywood Reporter |date=January 28, 2013 |accessdate=May 3, 2014 | archivedate= March 31, 2014 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20140331153816/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/paul-giamatti-talks-play-rhino-415899 | url-status =live}}</ref> Giamatti also indicated in an October 2013 interview that he would return in ''The Amazing Spider-Man 3'' as well.<ref>Nicholson, Max (October 3, 2013). [http://www.ign.com/articles/2013/10/03/paul-giamatti-will-be-back-for-amazing-spider-man-3 \"Paul Giamatti Will be Back for Amazing Spider-Man 3\"]. [[IGN]].</ref> On February 27, 2013, [[Chris Cooper (actor)|Chris Cooper]] was cast as [[Green Goblin|Norman Osborn]].<ref name=\"Norman casting\">{{cite web|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/amazing-spider-man-chris-cooper-424874|title='Amazing Spider-Man 2': Chris Cooper to Play Green Goblin|last=Siegel|first=Tatiana|work=The Hollywood Reporter|date=February 27, 2013}}</ref>\n\nBy October 10, 2012, [[Shailene Woodley]] was in talks for the role of [[Mary Jane Watson]].<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.eonline.com/news/353151/shailene-woodley-in-talks-for-amazing-spider-man-sequel |last=Finn | first=Natalie|title=Shailene Woodley In Talks for Amazing Spider Man Sequel |publisher=E! |accessdate=October 11, 2012 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20121114033410/http://www.eonline.com/news/353151/shailene-woodley-in-talks-for-amazing-spider-man-sequel | archivedate = November 14, 2012 | url-status=live|date=October 11, 2012 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Kit | first=Borys|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/shailene-woodley-talks-spider-man-377915 |title=Shailene Woodley in Talks for 'Spider-Man 2' |work=The Hollywood Reporter| date = November 17, 2011 |accessdate=October 11, 2012}}</ref> By March 14, 2013, Woodley had concluded filming her small role.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://splashpage.mtv.com/?p=75374 |title='Amazing Spider-Man 2': Shailene Woodley Finishes Shooting Sequel |publisher=[[MTV News]] |date=March 14, 2013|accessdate=April 2, 2013 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20130402230701/http://splashpage.mtv.com/?p=75374|archivedate=April 2, 2013 | url-status=live}}</ref> Garfield recalled, \"I think all of [those scenes] were in our backyards. We had two or three scenes with me talking over the fence, and there was one with us riding together on a motorcycle that we never got to shoot.\"<ref name=newsday-timessquare>{{cite news|url=http://www.newsday.com/entertainment/movies/the-amazing-spider-man-2-stars-talk-long-island-s-wild-times-square-set-1.7875942 |title='The Amazing Spider-Man 2' stars talk Long Island's 'wild' Times Square set |author-link= Frank Lovece |first=Frank |last=Lovece |work=[[Newsday]] |location=[[New York City|New York]] / [[Long Island]] |date=April 30, 2014 |archivedate=May 3, 2014 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6PHoz1coh?url=http://www.newsday.com/entertainment/movies/the-amazing-spider-man-2-stars-talk-long-island-s-wild-times-square-set-1.7875942 |url-status=live }} {{subscription}}</ref> By mid-June, Mary Jane was cut from the film, with director Webb explaining it as \"a creative decision to streamline the story and focus on Peter and Gwen and their relationship.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/amazing-spider-man-2-shailene-571744|title=Shailene Woodley Cut From 'Amazing Spider-Man 2'|last=Kit|first=Borys|work=The Hollywood Reporter|date=June 19, 2013|accessdate=June 19, 2013}}</ref>\n\n===Filming===\n{{Quote box\n| width = 25%\n| align = right\n| quote = This project had the highest level of detail incorporated into digital environments that we'd ever done. The human characters were finished to a very high degree. We had to do a very realistic version of Emma Stone. Spider-Man and Gwen are involved in stunts that would have been very dangerous if real.\n| source = \u2014Jerome Chen \u2013 VFX supervisor of Sony Imageworks<ref name=vfxjer>{{cite web|url=http://www.dailynews.com/arts-and-entertainment/20140429/the-amazing-spider-man-2-emphasizes-special-effects-spectacle|title='The Amazing Spider-Man 2' emphasizes special effects, spectacle|work=[[Daily News (New York)|Daily News]]|last=Adam|first=Poulisse|date=April 29, 2014}}</ref>}}\n\n[[File:Rochester - Main Street looking east.jpg|thumb|left|Major scenes were shot in Rochester.]]\nOn February 4, 2013, Marc Webb posted on [[Twitter]] that principal photography had begun and that the sequel was being shot on [[35mm movie film|35mm film]] in the [[anamorphic format]],<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.digitalspy.com/movies/spider-man/news/a456336/amazing-spider-man-2-begins-shooting-on-film-says-marc-webb/ | title='Amazing Spider-Man 2' begins shooting on film, says Marc Webb | publisher=Digital Spy | work=DS desk | date=February 5, 2013 | accessdate=March 31, 2016 | last= Armitage |first= Hugh}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cinemablend.com/new/Amazing-Spider-Man-2-Has-Started-Production-35526.html |title=The Amazing Spider-Man 2 Has Started Production |publisher=CinemaBlend.com |accessdate=February 7, 2013|date=February 4, 2013 }}</ref> instead of being filmed [[Digital cinematography|digitally]] as the preceding film was. Sony revealed this would be the first ''Spider-Man'' film to be filmed entirely in New York State, including a car-chase scene that was filmed in [[Rochester, New York|Rochester]] because the speed laws are less restrictive in upstate New York.<ref name=wsj-march12>{{cite web|url=https://online.wsj.com/news/articles/SB10001424127887323826704578356840396252864|title=Tax-Policy Web Lures 'Spider-Man' Film Here|last=Kusisto|first=Laura|date=March 12, 2013|accessdate=March 13, 2013}}</ref>\nIt became the largest film production ever in New York State.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.governor.ny.gov/press/03132013cuomo-announces-spiderman-movie-ny|title=Governor Cuomo Announces \"The Amazing Spider-Man 2\" to Be the Largest Movie Production Shot in New York|publisher=Office of Governor Andrew M. Cuomo |date=March 13, 2013|accessdate=May 3, 2014 | archivedate=March 7, 2014 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20140307015722/http://www.governor.ny.gov/press/03132013cuomo-announces-spiderman-movie-ny | url-status=live}}</ref> The decision to film in [[Williamsburg, Brooklyn]] near the [[Passover]] holiday caused some controversy, as critics believed that this was culturally insensitive, and would cause problems with parking.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.dnainfo.com/new-york/20130314/williamsburg/hasidic-leaders-fight-culturally-insensitive-passover-spider-man-shoot | title=Hasidic Leaders Fight 'Culturally Insensitive' Passover 'Spider-Man' Shoot | publisher=DNAinfo.com | last=Hoffman | first=Meredith | date=March 14, 2013 | accessdate=April 2, 2013 | url-status=dead | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130402223609/http://www.dnainfo.com/new-york/20130314/williamsburg/hasidic-leaders-fight-culturally-insensitive-passover-spider-man-shoot | archivedate=April 2, 2013 | df=mdy-all }}</ref> The filming company decided to work with the community and then agreed to adjust its production activities for Passover.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://pix11.com/2013/03/15/plan-for-the-amazing-spider-man-2-to-shoot-in-hasidic-williamsburg-at-passover-spins-web-of-controversy/#ixzz2PLfKS6KS | title=Plan for 'The Amazing Spider-Man 2' to shoot in Hasidic Williamsburg at Passover spins web of controversy | publisher=pix11.com | date=March 15, 2013 | accessdate=April 2, 2013 | last=Mercogliano | first = Ann }}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.nydailynews.com/new-york/spider-man-won-film-passover-article-1.1293556 | title='Let my people park': pol persuades Columbia Pictures not to film 'Spider-Man' during Passover | work=[[Daily News (New York)|Daily News]] | accessdate=March 20, 2013 | last=Beekman | first= Daniel | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131203233037/http://www.nydailynews.com/new-york/spider-man-won-film-passover-article-1.1293556 | archivedate=December 3, 2013 | url-status =live}}</ref> The producers had assembled a 200-person crew for the 10-day shoot in Rochester, with a total number of 250 local crew members and 150 local extras.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.democratandchronicle.com/story/news/2014/04/29/benefitted-spider-man/8491851/ | title='Spider-Man 2' shoot brought positives, negatives | publisher=[[Democrat and Chronicle]] | work=DC Staff | date=April 30, 2014 | author=E. Freile, Victoria | accessdate=April 1, 2016}}</ref> The prominent scenes were shot mostly on Main Street of Rochester and were digitally remastered to look like [[New York City]].<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.democratandchronicle.com/story/news/2014/04/29/rochesters-amazing-spider-man-cameo-coming/8493427/ | title=Rochester's 'Amazing Spider-Man 2' cameo is coming | publisher=[[Democrat and Chronicle]] | work=DC Staff | date=April 30, 2014 | accessdate=April 1, 2016 | author=E. Freile, Victoria}}</ref>\n\nOn June 25, Webb posted on Twitter that filming was completed.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://collider.com/amazing-spider-man-2-filming-wraps-video/ | title=Shooting Wraps on 'The Amazing Spider-Man 2'; Director Marc Webb Posts Impressive Short Video from the 100th Day of Filming | publisher=Collider | date=June 25, 2013 | accessdate=June 25, 2013 | author=Goldberg, Matt}}</ref> Soundstage work was done at [[Grumman Studios]] and Gold Coast Studios, both in [[Bethpage, New York]], and at the Marcy Armory in Brooklyn.<ref name=wsj-march12 /><ref>{{cite news | url = http://www.newsday.com/business/spider-man-sequel-films-at-grumman-gold-coast-studios-1.4795442 | title = 'Spider-Man' sequel films at Grumman, Gold Coast Studios | work = [[Newsday]] | date=March 11, 2013 | first= Lisa | last= Du | accessdate= January 23, 2014}}</ref>\n\n====Special effects====\n[[File:1 times square night 2013.jpg|thumb|left|The VFX design of Times Square, where the battle of Spider-Man and Electro takes place, took one year.<ref name=tsbattle/>]]\n[[Sony Pictures Imageworks]] designed the special effects for the film.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.imageworks.com/shows.php?p=current-shows&s=amazingspiderman2|title=The Amazing Spiderman 2 - Imageworks|publisher=[[Sony Pictures Imageworks]]|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160405133857/http://www.imageworks.com/shows.php?p=current-shows&s=amazingspiderman2|archivedate=April 5, 2016}}</ref> The digital composition of the film, including the scene where the battle of Spider-Man and Electro in [[Times Square]], took one year to complete.<ref name=tsbattle>{{cite web|url=http://www.digitaltrends.com/gaming/visual-effects-techniques-amazing-spider-man-2-will-make-true-believers-us/|title=How Spider-Man 2's FX team embraced fantasy without forgetting physics|publisher=Digital Trends|last=Devin|first=Connors|date=May 3, 2014}}</ref> The sets of Times Square were built in Gold Coast Studios with the [[chroma key|green screens]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.newsday.com/entertainment/movies/the-amazing-spider-man-2-stars-talk-long-island-s-wild-times-square-set-1.7875942|title='The Amazing Spider-Man 2' stars talk Long Island's 'wild' Times Square set|publisher=[[Newsday]]|last=Frank|first=Lovece|date= May 1, 2014}}</ref> and most of the scenes were digitally re-designed by computer.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://thecreatorsproject.vice.com/blog/behind-the-creation-and-destruction-of-a-digital-times-square-in-the-amazing-spider-man-2|title=Behind The Scenes Of The CGI Times Square In 'The Amazing Spider-Man 2'|publisher=News Creator|last=Michael|first=Hafford|date=May 27, 2014}}</ref> The photography and VFX team took over 36,000 photos of the Times Square in order to re-create the location digitally. In addition, the animation team captured over 100 billboards during the photography process.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://redesignreport.com/movie-friday-amazing-spider-man-2-depicts-times-square-like-never-before/|title=Movie Friday: The Amazing Spider-Man 2 Depicts Times Square Like Never Before|publisher=Re-Designer report|date=May 9, 2014|archiveurl=http://www.digitaltrends.com/gaming/visual-effects-techniques-amazing-spider-man-2-will-make-true-believers-us/|archivedate=May 3, 2014}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Jamie Foxx as Electro.jpg|thumb|Jamie Foxx as Electro. According to the actor, the make-up part was the most difficult phase during filming.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.foxnews.com/tech/2014/05/01/how-jamie-foxx-turned-into-spiderman-2s-electro.html|title=How Jamie Foxx turned into 'Spider-Man 2's' Electro|publisher=[[Fox News]]|last=Maegan|first=Murphy|date=May 1, 2014}}</ref>]]\nThe film was [[2D to 3D conversion|post-converted from 2D to 3D]], in part because the production team wanted to shoot [[35mm movie film|35mm film]]. Dan Mindel used Kodak Vision3 500T 5219 and 200T 5213, while the second unit shot day exteriors on Kodak Vision3 50D 5203.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.studiodaily.com/2014/05/10-film-facts-the-amazing-spider-man-2/|title=10 Film Facts: The Amazing Spider-Man 2|publisher=Studio Daily|last=Bryant|first=Frazer|date=May 6, 2014}}</ref> During the production, 20 layers of lightning CGI effects were applied to depict Electro. Jamie Foxx was photographed as Electro by KNB EFX team and the skin colors used to show the moods of the character.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/behind-screen/how-amazing-spider-man-2-700979|title=How 'The Amazing Spider-Man 2' VFX Team Brought Electro to Life|work=The Hollywood Reporter|last=Carolyn|first=Giardana|date=May 3, 2014}}</ref> A total number of 1,600 visual effects shots of the film was originally filmed in [[2K resolution]] and then converted into [[4K resolution]] with the help of [[Film colorization|color grading]].<ref name=mamaa/> To give the visual effects a realistic look, sound designers Addison Teague and Eric Norris and re-recording mixers Paul Massey and David Giammarco [[Audio mixing (recorded music)|mixed]] the background music using [[Auro 11.1]] [[Cinematic techniques#Sound|cinema sound technology]] and the film's soundtrack was remixed using [[Dolby Atmos]], Auro and [[Dolby Digital|Dolby 5.1]].<ref name=mamaa>{{cite web | url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/behind-screen/amazing-spider-man-2-behind-700687 | title='Amazing Spider-Man 2:' Behind the Scenes of Sony's 4K Web | work=The Hollywood Reporter | publisher=Prometheus Global Media | date=May 2, 2014 | accessdate=March 31, 2016 | author=Giardina, Carolyn}}</ref>\n\n===Post-production===\nThe film was mixed in [[Auro 11.1]] and [[Dolby Atmos]] in the converted [[William Holden]] Theater. The mix for both was completed by Paul Massey and David Giammarco.<ref name=mamaa/><ref name=\"AuroAtmos\">{{cite press release|url=http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/the-amazing-spider-man-2-gets-state-of-the-art-sound-as-filmmakers-mix-in-dolby-atmos-and-auro-111-by-barco-242640051.html|title='The Amazing Spider-Man 2' Gets State-Of-The-Art Sound As Filmmakers Mix In Dolby Atmos And Auro 11.1 By Barco|publisher=[[Sony Pictures Entertainment]]|date=January 29, 2014|accessdate=March 1, 2014 | archivedate= February 2, 2014 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20140202193512/http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/the-amazing-spider-man-2-gets-state-of-the-art-sound-as-filmmakers-mix-in-dolby-atmos-and-auro-111-by-barco-242640051.html | url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nA mid-credit teaser scene from ''[[X-Men: Days of Future Past]]'' was added to the film after its London premiere, due to an existing deal between Webb and [[20th Century Fox]], in which Fox allowed Webb to direct the film if Sony would promote the [[X-Men]] film for free.<ref name=\"VarietyXMen\">{{cite web |url=https://variety.com/2014/film/news/the-secret-deal-behind-spider-man-2-plugging-the-x-men-exclusive-1201158216/|title=The Secret Deal Behind 'Spider-Man 2' Plugging the 'X-Men' (EXCLUSIVE)|work=Variety|date=April 16, 2014|accessdate=April 16, 2014}}</ref> The scene, set during the [[Vietnam War]], shows [[Mystique (comics)|Mystique]] ([[Jennifer Lawrence]]), a rogue mutant, trying to infiltrate a military camp led by [[William Stryker]] ([[Josh Helman]]) in an attempt to recruit fellow mutants [[Havok (comics)|Havok]] ([[Lucas Till]]) and [[Toad (comics)|Toad]] (Evan Jonigkeit).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ign.com/articles/2014/04/16/thereas-an-x-men-days-of-future-past-scene-during-amazing-spider-man-2as-end-credits |title=There's an X-Men: Days of Future Past Scene During Amazing Spider-Man 2's End Credits |first=Scott |last=Collura |work=[[IGN.com]]|date=April 16, 2014 |accessdate=April 17, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/spider-man-2-post-credit-696957 |title='Spider-Man 2' Post-Credit 'X-Men' Cameo Explained |first=Graeme |last=McMillan |work=The Hollywood Reporter|date=April 16, 2014 |accessdate=April 17, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.empireonline.com/news/story.asp?NID=40776 |title=See An X-Men: Days Of Future Past Sting On Amazing Spider-Man 2 |first=Helen |last=O'Hara |work=[[Empire (film magazine)|Empire]] |publisher=[[Bauer Media Group|Bauer Consumer Media]] |date=April 16, 2014 |accessdate=April 17, 2014}}</ref> The scene's inclusion sparked confusion among some viewers in the United Kingdom, who thought it meant an X-Men\u2013Spider-Man crossover film was being planned, based on how [[Marvel Studios]] and [[Walt Disney Studios (division)|Disney]] use [[Post-credits scene|codas]] within the [[Marvel Cinematic Universe]] to promote future films.<ref name=\"VarietyXMen\" />\n\n===Music===\n{{Main|The Amazing Spider-Man 2 (soundtrack)}}\n{| border=\"0\"  style=\"float:right; font-size:100%; color:black; width:130px;\"\n|-\n|\n{{Listen\n |filename     = ItsOnAgain.ogg\n |title        = \"It's On Again\"\n |description  =\n}} \n|}\n{{Anchor|Soundtrack}}\nOn July 20, 2013, Webb announced that [[Hans Zimmer]] would be composing the music for the film, replacing [[James Horner]], the composer of the first film.<ref name=\"Goblins,Zimmer\">{{cite web|url=http://cinemablend.com/new/Amazing-Spider-Man-2-Must-Read-Marc-Webb-Goblins-Internet-Rumors-Thinking-Bigger-38620-p2.html|title=Amazing Spider-Man 2 Must Read: Marc Webb On Goblins, Internet Rumors And 'Thinking Bigger'|publisher=Cinema Blend|date=July 20, 2013}}</ref> On October 25, 2013, [[Pharrell Williams]] revealed to ''Billboard'' that he would co-compose the score with Zimmer.<ref name=\"billboard\">{{cite web |url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2013/10/28/pharell-hans-zimmer-spiderman_n_4171035.html?ir=India&adsSiteOverride=in|title=Pharrell & Hans Zimmer Will Write The 'Amazing Spider-Man 2' Score |publisher=[[The Huffington Post]] |first=Kelsey |last=McQuade|date=October 29, 2013 |accessdate=November 17, 2015}}</ref> Webb and Zimmer formed a supergroup with Williams, [[Johnny Marr]], [[Mike Einziger]] and former [[Eurythmics|Eurythmic]], [[David A. Stewart]], to create the music for the sequel.<ref name=\"hollywoodreporter.com\">{{cite web|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/marc-webb-hans-zimmer-form-652222 |title=Marc Webb, Hans Zimmer Form Supergroup for 'Amazing Spider-Man 2' |work=The Hollywood Reporter |date=2013-10-31 |accessdate=2014-06-04}}</ref> Eventually, Stewart did not participate in the film's music, and the supergroup, credited as ''The Magnificent Six'' (a reference to the [[Sinister Six]]) was composed of Williams, Marr, Einziger, [[Junkie XL]], Steve Mazzaro and Andrew Kawczynski assisting Zimmer. The soundtrack for the film was released on April 22, 2014 by [[Columbia Records]] and [[Madison Gate Records]].<ref>{{cite press release|url=http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/the-amazing-spider-man-2-to-include-its-on-again-by-alicia-keys-featuring-kendrick-lamar-written-by-pharrell-williams-alicia-keys-hans-zimmer-and-kendrick-lamar-249701151.html |title=\"The Amazing Spider-Man 2\" To Include \"It's On Again\" by Alicia Keys Featuring Kendrick Lamar Written by Pharrell Williams, Alicia Keys, Hans Zimmer, and Kendrick Lamar |publisher=[[Sony Music Entertainment]]/[[Sony Pictures Entertainment]]/[[Marvel Entertainment]]|agency=[[PR Newswire]] |accessdate=April 7, 2014}}</ref> Hans Zimmer described his work for this film as different from previous works by him, thus revealing one of the themes for the film, which was first heard on the website.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://screenrant.com/amazing-spider-man-2-theme-soundtrack-hans-zimmer/|title=Hans Zimmer's 'Amazing Spider-Man 2' Theme Revealed?|publisher=Screen Rant|first=Anthony|last=Vieira|accessdate=April 12, 2014}}</ref>\n\nOn March 31, 2014, a track called \"[[It's On Again]]\" was uploaded to [[SoundCloud]].<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/earshot/audio-alicia-keys-kendrick-lamar-692266 | title=Alicia Keys, Kendrick Lamar Release 'Amazing Spider-Man 2' Song (Audio) | work=The Hollywood Reporter | publisher=Prometheus Global Media | date=March 31, 2014 | accessdate=March 31, 2016 | author=Lee, Ashley}}</ref> It features vocals by [[Kendrick Lamar]] and [[Alicia Keys]]. Keys announced the song on Twitter and credited Zimmer and Williams, along with Lamar and herself for the song, indicating the song as a part of the film's soundtrack.<ref name=song11>{{cite web | url=http://www.mtv.com/news/1723970/alicia-keys-kendrick-lamar-pharrell-its-on-again-amazing-spider-man-2/ | title=ALICIA KEYS, PHARRELL AND KENDRICK LAMAR WARN 'IT'S ON AGAIN' | publisher=[[MTV News]] | work=MTV news desk | date=March 12, 2014 | accessdate=March 31, 2016 | author=Kaufman, Gil}}</ref> Webb described the song as \"upbeat and exciting\".<ref name=song11/>\n\n==Marketing==\nThe release of the film in the United Kingdom was moved to April 16, 2014, two days ahead of its original April 18 date.<ref>{{cite web|last=Wales|first=George|title=Amazing Spider-Man 2 moves UK release forward|url=http://www.totalfilm.com/news/amazing-spider-man-2-moves-uk-release-forward|work=Total Film|accessdate=April 9, 2014|date=April 9, 2014}}</ref> [[Deadline Hollywood|Deadline]] reported that, in addition to the production budget, the film's marketing budget was $180\u2013190 million.<ref name=\"International-Gross\">{{cite web|url=http://www.deadline.com/2014/04/amazing-spider-man-2-box-office-international-launch/|title='Amazing Spider-Man 2' Swinging Strong In International Debut As It Casts Global Web|last=Busch|first=Anita|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]] | date = April 17, 2014|accessdate=April 18, 2014 | archivedate= April 21, 2014 | url-status=live | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20140421162344/http://www.deadline.com/2014/04/amazing-spider-man-2-box-office-international-launch/}}</ref>\n[[File:Andrew Garfield and Jamie Foxx by Gage Skidmore.jpg|right|250px|thumb|Andrew Garfield and Jamie Foxx at the 2013 [[San Diego Comic-Con International]] promoting ''The Amazing Spider-Man 2''.]]\n\nOn July 17, 2013, Sony released a clip from the film with the first released footage of Jamie Foxx as Electro to encourage attendance at the panel, at the [[San Diego Comic-Con]] International.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.superherohype.com/news/articles/178181-watch-the-amazing-spider-man-2-comic-con-hall-h-promo|title=Watch The Amazing Spider-Man 2 Comic-Con Hall H Promo!|publisher=SuperHero Hype|date=July 17, 2013}}</ref> At the panel they premiered a four-minute trailer, which was not publicly released but eventually leaked on the internet. Viral marketing for the film included a version of the ''[[Daily Bugle]]'' on the blogging service [[Tumblr]], which included references to [[Kathryn Cushing (Marvel Comics)|Kate Cushing]], [[Sin-Eater (comics)#Stanley Carter|Detective Stan Carter]], the \"[[Frederick Foswell|Big Man]]\", [[Isabel Bunsen (Marvel Comics)|Izzy Bunsen]], [[Joy Mercado (Marvel Comics)|Joy Mercado]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://thedailybugle.tumblr.com/post/69208620209/by-joy-mercado-some-people-have-visions-of-the |title=The Daily Bugle, By Joy Mercado Some people have visions of the |publisher=Thedailybugle.tumblr.com |date=December 6, 2013 |accessdate=February 14, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Mercado |first=Joy |url=http://thedailybugle.tumblr.com/post/68949122520/by-joy-mercado-oscorp-industries-wants-to-usher |title=Tech Beat: Exploring Mobility |publisher=Thedailybugle.tumblr.com |date=December 3, 2013 |accessdate=May 3, 2014}}</ref> [[Donald Menken]], the [[Vulture (Marvel Comics)|Vulture]], [[Hydro-Man]], [[Spencer Smythe]], [[Ned Leeds]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://thedailybugle.tumblr.com/post/72012128469/by-ned-leeds-city-bureau-smash-the-tail-of-a |title=The Daily Bugle, By Ned Leeds, City Bureau Smash the tail of a |publisher=Thedailybugle.tumblr.com |date=January 2, 2014 |accessdate=February 14, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Leeds |first=Ned |url=http://thedailybugle.tumblr.com/post/68311370715/by-ned-leeds-city-bureau-the-nypd-are-the-citys |title=Shake, Rattle and Rob |publisher=Thedailybugle.tumblr.com |date=November 27, 2013 |accessdate=May 3, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://thedailybugle.tumblr.com/post/64888475045/by-ned-leeds-city-bureau-a-trial-date-has-been|title=Cold-Blooded Killer?|last=Leeds|first=Ned|publisher=Sony Pictures Entertainment|date=October 23, 2013|accessdate=October 24, 2013}}</ref> [[She-Venom#Fictional character biography|Anne Weying]], [[J. Jonah Jameson]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://thedailybugle.tumblr.com/post/65562508873/an-editorial-from-daily-bugle-publisher-j-jonah |title=Spider-Man: Threat or Menace? |publisher=Thedailybugle.tumblr.com |date=October 30, 2013 |accessdate=May 3, 2014}}</ref> [[Shocker (comics)|Shocker]], [[Alistair Smythe]], [[Doctor Octopus]], [[Eddie Brock]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://thedailybugle.tumblr.com/post/69810901835/by-eddie-brock-what-began-as-a-mob-shoot-out |title=The Daily Bugle, By Eddie Brock What began as a mob shoot-out |publisher=Thedailybugle.tumblr.com |date=December 12, 2013 |accessdate=February 14, 2014}}</ref> [[Enforcers (comics)|The Enforcers]], and [[Puma (comics)|Puma]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://thedailybugle.tumblr.com/post/55883355856/whats-next-for-the-nypd-2|title=What is Next for the NYPD?|last=Cushing|first=Kate|publisher=Sony Pictures Entertainment|date=July 18, 2013|accessdate=October 19, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://screenrant.com/amazing-spider-man-2-viral-marketing-more-villains/|title='The Amazing Spider-Man 2' Viral Marketing Teases More Villains|last=Frappier|first=Rob|publisher=ScreenRant|date=October 15, 2013|accessdate=October 19, 2013}}</ref> Marc Webb posted a photo on Twitter with a message written in Dwarven language revealing that the first trailer would debut prior to 3D screenings of ''[[The Hobbit: The Desolation of Smaug]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cinemablend.com/new/Amazing-Spider-Man-2-First-Trailer-Debut-With-Hobbit-3D-40076.html|title=The Amazing Spider-Man 2's First Trailer to Debut prior to The Hobbit|last=Eisenberg|first=Eric|publisher=Cinema Blend|date=October 29, 2013|accessdate=October 29, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://comicbook.com/blog/2013/10/29/amazing-spider-man-2-trailer-coming-next-month-with-the-hobbit-part-2/|title=Amazing Spider-Man 2 Trailer Coming in December With The Hobbit Part 2|last=Burlingame|first=Russ|publisher=Comicbook.com|date=October 29, 2013|accessdate=October 29, 2013}}</ref>\n\nOn December 8, 2013, it was announced that new footage from the film would be presented during [[Times Square Ball|New Year's Eve festivities]] at New York City's [[Times Square]].<ref name=nydn-timessquare>{{cite web|title=EXCLUSIVE: Spider-Man to make an appearance at Times Square on New Year's Eve|url=http://www.nydailynews.com/new-york/spidey-slings-new-year-article-1.1541017|work=Daily News|location=New York|accessdate=December 9, 2013}}</ref> The film was further promoted during the [[World Wide Fund for Nature]] (WWF) \"[[Earth Hour]]\" campaign. The cast was present at the launch of the 2014 event in Singapore.<ref>{{cite web|last=Rodger|first=Kate|title=Amazing Spider-Man 2 launches Earth Hour 2014 in Singapore|url=http://www.3news.co.nz/Amazing-Spider-Man-2-launches-Earth-Hour-2014-in-Singapore/tabid/418/articleID/338095/Default.aspx|work=[[3 News]]|accessdate=March 31, 2014|date=April 8, 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140408223337/http://www.3news.co.nz/Amazing-Spider-Man-2-launches-Earth-Hour-2014-in-Singapore/tabid/418/articleID/338095/Default.aspx|archive-date=April 8, 2014|url-status=dead}}</ref> [[Disney Consumer Products and Interactive Media|Disney Consumer Products]] announced a merchandise product line for the film at the [[American International Toy Fair]] on February 17, 2014.<ref>{{cite news|title=Disney Consumer Products Ready to Capture Boys' Imaginations and Dominate Toy Aisles in 2014|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/2014/02/17/ny-disney-consumer-idUSnBw175620a+100+BSW20140217|accessdate=May 1, 2014|newspaper=The Reuters|date=February 17, 2014}}</ref>\n\nIn March 2014, [[Gameloft]] and Marvel announced the launch of a mobile game [[The Amazing Spider-Man 2 (2014 video game)|of the same name]] for smartphones and tablets.<ref>{{cite press release|url=http://marvel.com/news/video_games/2014/3/11/22116/gameloft_and_marvel_swing_back_onto_smartphones_and_tablets_with_the_amazing_spider-man_2 |title=Gameloft and Marvel Swing Back Onto Smartphones and Tablets with The Amazing Spider-Man 2 |publisher=Marvel |date=March 11, 2014 |accessdate=May 3, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|first=Spencer |last=Perry |url=http://www.superherohype.com/news/294723-gameloft-and-marvel-announce-the-amazing-spider-man-2-mobile-game |title=Gameloft and Marvel Announce The Amazing Spider-Man 2 Mobile Game |publisher=SuperHeroHype |date=March 11, 2014 |accessdate=May 3, 2014}}</ref> It was released on consoles afterward.<ref>{{cite web | url = http://kotaku.com/the-amazing-spider-man-2-game-is-coming-out-on-xbox-one-1569354844 | accessdate = April 29, 2014 | date = April 29, 2014 | publisher = Kotaku | title = The Amazing Spider-Man 2 Game Is Coming Out on Xbox One, After All | author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.-->}}</ref> [[Kellogg's]] released an application featuring the film.<ref>{{cite press release|title=Kellogg Releases Game App for The Amazing Spider-Man 2 Movie, Partners with Sony for New Sweepstakes|url=http://www.marketwatch.com/story/kellogg-releases-game-app-for-the-amazing-spider-man-2-movie-partners-with-sony-for-new-sweepstakes-2014-04-21 |publisher=[[Kellogg Company]] |accessdate=May 1, 2014|date=April 21, 2014}}</ref> [[Evian]] served as a promotional partner of the film. On April 1, 2014, the brand released an advertisement \"The Amazing Baby & Me 2\" featuring Spider-Man and a baby version of him, as a follow-up to their original \"Baby & Me\" campaign.<ref>{{cite web|last=Graser|first=Marc|title=Baby Spider-Man Dances for Evian|url=https://variety.com/2014/digital/news/baby-spider-man-dances-for-evian-1201151726/|work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|accessdate=April 7, 2014|date=April 2, 2014}}</ref> The film partnered with [[NBCUniversal]] for advertising. Spots for the film appeared on Bravo, E!, USA, Syfy, Telemundo, and mun2. A customized page was created on Fandango.<ref>{{cite web|last=Steinberg|first=Brian|title='Spider-Man 2' To Swing Across NBCU's TV Networks In Promotional Pact|url=https://variety.com/2014/tv/news/spider-man-2-to-swing-across-nbcus-tv-networks-in-promotional-pact-1201160000/|work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|accessdate=May 1, 2014|date=April 21, 2014}}</ref> In May 2014, Marvel announced that Spider-Man's costume from the film would be shown within ''[[Marvel: Avengers Alliance]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://marvel.com/news/movies/2014/5/1/22439/learn_more_about_the_amazing_spider-man_2_costume_before_it_hits_marvel_avengers_alliance|title=Learn More About the Amazing Spider-Man 2 Costume Before it Hits Marvel: Avengers Alliance|last=Strom|first=Marc|publisher=Marvel|date=May 1, 2014|accessdate=May 1, 2014}}</ref>\n\n==Home media==\nThe film has an alternate ending in which [[Spider-Man|Peter Parker]]'s father meets Peter at Gwen's resting place.<ref name=petedad>{{cite web|url=http://www.techtimes.com/articles/12816/20140812/amazing-spider-man-2-includes-telling-deleted-scene.htm|title=Watch: 'Amazing Spider-Man 2' alternate ending (Video)|publisher=Tech Times|last=Jarret|first=Kruse|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160401102848/http://www.techtimes.com/articles/12816/20140812/amazing-spider-man-2-includes-telling-deleted-scene.htm|archivedate=April 1, 2016|date=August 12, 2015}}</ref> Creative agency Deckhouse Digital was hired to produce several animated [[GIF]]s ahead of the [[DVD]]/[[Blu-ray]] release as part of a sponsored ad campaign on Tumblr.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://deckhousedigital.com/tagged/spiderman/ |title=Animated GIFs and Motion Poster for The Amazing Spider-Man 2 |accessdate=August 21, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://theamazingspidermanblog.com/ |title=The Amazing Spider-Man 2 on Tumblr |accessdate=August 21, 2014}}</ref> ''The Amazing Spider-Man 2'' was released by [[Sony Pictures Home Entertainment]] for [[Digital distribution|digital download]] on August 5, 2014 and was released on Blu-ray, [[Blu-ray#Blu-ray 3D|Blu-ray 3D]] and DVD on August 19, 2014.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://insidemovies.ew.com/2014/06/16/amazing-spider-man-2-blu-ray/|title='Amazing Spider-Man 2' Blu-ray gets release date, might have tantalizing deleted scenes|last= Labrecque|first=Jeff|work=Entertainment Weekly|date=June 16, 2014|accessdate=June 16, 2014}}</ref> ''The Amazing Spider-Man 2'' was included in The Spider-Man Legacy Collection which includes five Spider-Man films in a 4K UHD Blu-ray collection, which was released on October 17, 2017.<ref>{{Citation|title=Spider-Man Legacy Collection 4K Blu-ray|url=http://www.blu-ray.com/movies/Spider-Man-Legacy-Collection-4K-Blu-ray/186849/|accessdate=2018-05-22}}</ref> ''The Amazing Spider-Man 2'' was released on 4K UHD Blu-ray on March 1, 2016, this includes one film only and is the only Spider-Man film in the Spider-Man Legacy Collection to have a solo 4K Blu-ray release until early 2018.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://ultrahd.highdefdigest.com/30701/theamazingspiderman2ultrahdbluray.html|title=The Amazing Spider-Man 2 - Ultra HD Blu-ray Ultra HD Review {{!}} High Def Digest|website=ultrahd.highdefdigest.com |access-date=2018-05-22}}</ref>\n\n==Reception==\n\n===Critical response===\nOn [[Rotten Tomatoes]], the film has an approval rating of 52% based on 302 reviews and an average rating of 5.81/10. The site's critical consensus reads, \"While the cast is outstanding and the special effects are top-notch, the latest installment of the Spidey saga suffers from an unfocused narrative and an overabundance of characters.\"<ref name=\"RT\">{{cite web |title=The Amazing Spider-Man 2 (2014) |url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/the_amazing_spider_man_2 |publisher=[[Fandango Media]] |work=[[Rotten Tomatoes]] |accessdate=July 3, 2019}}</ref> On [[Metacritic]], the film has a score of 53 out of 100 based on 50 critics, indicating \"mixed or average reviews\".<ref name=\"Meta\">{{cite web |url=https://www.metacritic.com/movie/the-amazing-spider-man-2 |publisher=[[CBS Interactive]] |title=The Amazing Spider-Man 2 Reviews |work=[[Metacritic]] |accessdate=September 6, 2018}}</ref> Audiences polled by [[CinemaScore]] gave the film an average grade of \"B+\" on an A+ to F scale, lower than the \"A\u2212\" earned by its predecessor.<ref name=\"CinemaScore\">{{cite web |url= https://www.cinemascore.com/publicsearch/index/title/ |title= Cinemascore |url-status= dead |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20181220122629/https://www.cinemascore.com/publicsearch/index/title/ |archive-date= 2018-12-20 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |date= 5 May 2014 |last1= Busch |first1= Anita |title= FINAL BOX OFFICE: 'Amazing Spider-Man 2' \u2013 $91.6M; 'The Other Woman' Holding Strong; 'Rio 2' Passes $100M |url= https://deadline.com/2014/05/amazing-spider-man-2-box-office-opening-big-debut-723393/ |website= Deadline |quote= B+ CinemaScore and an A- for those under 25 }}</ref>\n\nCriticism was directed at the script and length.<ref>{{cite journal |url=https://www.theatlantic.com/entertainment/archive/2014/05/the-amazing-spider-man-2/361552/ |title=''Spider-Man 2'': More Is (Much) Less |journal=[[The Atlantic]] |first=Christopher |last=Orr |date=May 2, 2014 |accessdate=May 23, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/goingoutguide/movies/the-amazing-spider-man-2-review-web-spinning-superhero-returns-with-mixed-results/2014/05/01/ff15f792-cfab-11e3-a6b1-45c4dffb85a6_story.html |title='The Amazing Spider-Man 2' review: Web-spinning superhero returns with mixed results |date=May 1, 2014 |newspaper=[[The Washington Post]] |first=Ann |last=Hornaday |accessdate=May 23, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.npr.org/2014/05/01/308607547/such-a-lovely-couple-if-only-the-supervillains-would-leave-them-alone |title=Such A Lovely Couple, If Only The Supervillains Would Leave Them Alone |publisher=[[NPR]] |date=May 1, 2014 |first=Ian |last=Buckwalter |accessdate=May 23, 2014}}</ref> However, the special effects, chemistry between Stone and Garfield, the action scenes, and Hans Zimmer's musical score received praise.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.seattletimes.com/entertainment/movies/lsquothe-amazing-spider-man-2rsquo-a-not-quite-amazing-installment/ |title='The Amazing Spider-Man 2': a not-quite-amazing installment |newspaper=[[The Seattle Times]] |date=May 1, 2014 |first=Moira |last=Macdonald |archivedate=March 31, 2016|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160331073219/http://www.seattletimes.com/entertainment/movies/lsquothe-amazing-spider-man-2rsquo-a-not-quite-amazing-installment/}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/life/movies/2014/04/30/amazing-spiderman-2-review/8309667/ |title='Spider-Man 2' spins web of chemistry, wit |newspaper=[[USA Today]] |date=May 2, 2014 |first=Claudia |last=Puig |accessdate=May 23, 2014}}</ref> Foxx's portrayal of Max Dillon/Electro was met with mixed reviews.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://movies.yahoo.com/blogs/movie-news/early-reviews--critics-tangled-over--the-amazing-spider-man-2--villains-213227297.html |title=Early Reviews: Critics Tangled Over 'The Amazing Spider-Man 2' Villains |date=April 9, 2014 |work=[[Yahoo! Movies]] |accessdate=July 23, 2014 |first=Bryan |last=Enk}}</ref>\n\nThe ''[[Los Angeles Times]]'' said, \"[The film is] overstuffed with plot lines, set pieces and villains, although stars Andrew Garfield and Emma Stone do their best to give the movie heart.\"<ref>{{cite news | last=Gettell | first=Oliver | url=http://www.latimes.com/entertainment/movies/moviesnow/la-et-mn-amazing-spider-man-2-movie-reviews-critics-20140502-story.html | title='The Amazing Spider-Man 2' spins out of control, reviews say | work=[[Los Angeles Times]] | date=May 2, 2014 | accessdate=May 28, 2014 }}</ref> Tim Robey of ''[[The Daily Telegraph|The Telegraph]]'' said, \"Marc Webb's Spider-Man sequel is overstuffed with high-voltage villains, but the sparks between Andrew Garfield and Emma Stone save the day\".<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/culture/film/filmreviews/10752688/The-Amazing-Spider-Man-2-review.html |title=The Amazing Spider-Man 2, review |newspaper=[[The Daily Telegraph]] |first=Tim |last=Robey |date=April 8, 2014 |accessdate=April 12, 2014}}</ref> Simon Reynolds of ''[[Digital Spy]]'' said, \"Peter's past, present and future all intertwine in a sequel that offers bang for your buck. That said you can't help [but] feel the franchise bean counters at work here thanks to all the ominous foreshadowing and unresolved character arcs. Too many cooks and all that&nbsp;...\".<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/movies/review/a563365/the-amazing-spider-man-2-review-andrew-garfield-leads-uneven-sequel.html |title=The Amazing Spider-Man 2 review: Andrew Garfield leads uneven sequel |work=Digital Spy |first=Simon |last=Reynolds |date=April 9, 2014 |accessdate=April 12, 2014}}</ref> Kim Newman of [[Empire (film magazine)|Empire]] scored the film three out of five stars, saying: \"A few too-broad gags aside\u2014and even these are in the funky spirit of '60s Marvel\u2014this is a satisfying second issue with thrills, heartbreak, gasps, and a perfectly judged slingshot ending.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.empireonline.com/reviews/reviewcomplete.asp?FID=137995|title=The Amazing Spider-Man 2 Movie Review |work=Empire Magazine |first=Kim |last=Newman |accessdate=June 1, 2014}}</ref> Leslie Felperin of ''[[The Hollywood Reporter]]'' said, \"The eponymous hero hits his super-heroic stride here, as does Andrew Garfield in the role, especially when Spider-Man's alter ego Peter Parker learns there's always some fine print in a contract with this many benefits. The plot gets itself tangled up in multiple villain strands, but in the main, this installment is emotionally weightier and more satisfying than its predecessor.\"<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/movie/amazing-spider-man-2/review/694460 |title=The Amazing Spider-Man 2: Film Review |work=The Hollywood Reporter |date=April 8, 2014 |first=Leslie |last=Felperin |accessdate=April 12, 2014}}</ref>\n\nGuy Lodge of ''[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]'' said, \"Redundancy remains a problem, but this overlong superhero sequel gets by on sound, fury and star chemistry.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2014/film/reviews/film-review-the-amazing-spider-man-2-1201154134/ |title=Film Review: 'The Amazing Spider-Man 2' |magazine=Variety |date=April 8, 2014 |first=Guy |last=Lodge |accessdate=April 12, 2014}}</ref> [[Richard Roeper]] gave the film a B+, stating that \"It's about 20 minutes too long and it's overstuffed with too many characters and too many subplots, but there's enough good stuff in ''The Amazing Spider-Man 2'' to warrant optimism about the next chapter of the franchise.\"<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.richardroeper.com/reviews/spiderman2.aspx |title=''The Amazing Spider-Man 2'' Review |last= Roeper |first= Richard |publisher=Richard Roeper & The Movies |date=May 2, 2014 |accessdate=May 3, 2014|author-link=Richard Roeper }}</ref> A negative review came from Peter Travers of ''[[Rolling Stone]]'', giving the film two stars out of four, he said: \"Things go wrong quickly with Amazing 2. Am I the only one who hates the word Amazing to describe a movie that isn't? Just asking.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/movies/reviews/the-amazing-spider-man-2-20140501 |title=Film Review: 'The Amazing Spider-Man 2' |magazine=Rolling Stone |first=Peter |last=Travers |date=May 1, 2014 |accessdate=June 19, 2014}}</ref> [[IGN]] reviewer Daniel Krupa gave 6.9/10 and wrote, \"''Amazing Spider-Man 2'' gets a lot right, yet there's a constant awkwardness to the machinery of its plot; you can almost hear the cogs turning. However, what's worse is that at times it becomes overtly patronising: there are flashing screens and computer voice-overs constantly telling you what something is or what something is doing, just in case the people in the back rows aren't paying attention, which feels at odds with the film's emotional intelligence.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ign.com/articles/2014/04/09/amazing-spider-man-2-review |title=THE AMAZING SPIDER-MAN 2 REVIEW |website=IGN |first=Krupa |last=Daniel |date=April 9, 2014 |accessdate=September 10, 2016}}</ref>\n\n===Box office===\n''The Amazing Spider-Man 2'' grossed $202.9 million in the United States and Canada and $506.1 million in other countries for a worldwide gross of $709 million.<ref name=\"mojo\"/> ''[[Deadline Hollywood]]'' calculated the net profit of the film to be $70.38 million, when factoring together all expenses and revenues for the film, making it one of the top 20 most profitable releases of 2014.<ref name=profits>{{cite web|url=http://deadline.com/2015/03/amazing-spider-man-2-profit-box-office-2014-1201389608/|title=No. 18 'Amazing Spider-Man 2' \u2013 2014 Most Valuable Movie Blockbuster Tournament|author=Mike Fleming Jr|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|date=March 10, 2015|accessdate=November 11, 2017}}</ref>\n\nThe film grossed $8.7 million on its early Thursday night showings.<ref>{{cite web|last=Mendelson|first=Scott|title=Thursday Box Office: 'Amazing Spider-Man 2' Spins $8.7M|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/scottmendelson/2014/05/02/thursday-box-office-amazing-spider-man-2-spins-8-7m/|work=Forbes|accessdate=May 5, 2014|date=May 2, 2014}}</ref> It finished its opening weekend in first place with $91.6 million, almost $30 million more than the opening-weekend gross of the [[The Amazing Spider-Man (2012 film)|first film]].<ref>{{cite news|last=Subers|first=Ray|url=http://boxofficemojo.com/news/?id=3837&p=.htm|title=Weekend Report: Franchise Fatigue Weighs Down 'Amazing Spider-Man 2'|website=[[Box Office Mojo]]|date=May 4, 2014}}</ref> In its second weekend the film grossed $35.5 million (falling 61%) and dropped to second at the box office behind newcomer ''[[Neighbors (2014 film)|Neighbors]]''. It was similar to the 61.5% second-week drop of ''[[Spider-Man 3]]'' in 2007.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.boxofficemojo.com/news/?id=3841&p=.htm|title=Weekend Report: 'Neighbors' Hazes 'Spider-Man'|website=[[Box Office Mojo]]|date=May 11, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |date= May 3, 2014 | first = Oliver| last = Gettell |title= 'Amazing Spider-Man 2': Five box-office bets for the web-slinger |url= http://www.latimes.com/entertainment/movies/moviesnow/la-et-mn-amazing-spider-man-2-five-box-office-bets-20140501,0,2247433.story|work=[[Los Angeles Times]] |accessdate= May 3, 2014}}</ref>\n\nOutside North America, ''The Amazing Spider-Man 2'' opened on April 16, 2014 to $2.73 million in the UK and to $190,000 in Belgium, while opening to $1.44 million in Australia and $1.11 million in Germany.<ref name=\"International-Gross2\">{{cite web|url=http://www.boxoffice.com/news/2014-04-17-the-amazing-spider-man-2-nets-big-opening-day-results-from-first-four-territories|title='The Amazing Spider-Man 2' Nets Big Opening Day Results From First Four Territories|publisher=BoxOffice|date=April 17, 2014|accessdate=April 18, 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140419012333/http://www.boxoffice.com/news/2014-04-17-the-amazing-spider-man-2-nets-big-opening-day-results-from-first-four-territories|archive-date=April 19, 2014|url-status=dead}}</ref> The film's release in India was the biggest opening weekend for an American film at that point with {{INRConvert|41|c}}. Its final box office collection was $13.44&nbsp;million there, one of the highest of all time by a Hollywood film.<ref>{{cite web|last=McClintock|first=Pamela|title=Box Office: 'Amazing Spider-Man 2' Kicks Off Summer With $92 Million Debut|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/box-office-amazing-spider-man-701103|work=The Hollywood Reporter|accessdate=May 5, 2014|date=May 4, 2014}}</ref> In China, the film played on 11,002 screens, which is the biggest release of any film in history.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Livesey|last2=Sakou|first1=Ben|first2=Anousha|title='Spider-Man' On-Screen Heroics Tempered at Ticket Windows|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2014-05-04/-spider-man-on-screen-heroics-tempered-at-cinema-ticket-window|work=[[Bloomberg News]]|accessdate=November 17, 2015|date=May 6, 2014}}</ref> On its opening day in Hong Kong, the film earned $1.23 million, the highest opening gross in the territory.<ref>{{cite web|last=Chu|first=Karen|title='The Amazing Spider-Man 2' Breaks Opening-Day Box-Office Record in Hong Kong|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/amazing-spider-man-2-breaks-700710|work=The Hollywood Reporter|accessdate=May 5, 2014|date=May 2, 2014}}</ref>\n\n===Accolades===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" \n! Award\n! Category\n! Recipient\n! Result\n! {{Abbr|Ref.|References}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"5\"| [[2014 Teen Choice Awards|Teen Choice Awards]]\n| [[Teen Choice Award for Choice Movie \u2013 Sci-Fi/Fantasy|Choice Movie: Sci-Fi/Fantasy]]\n| ''The Amazing Spider-Man 2''\n| {{nom}}\n| rowspan=\"5\" style=\"text-align:center;\"| <ref>{{cite web |url=https://movies.yahoo.com/news/teen-choice-awards-2014-nominees-revealed-163400995.html |title=Teen Choice Awards 2014 Nominees Revealed! |date=June 17, 2014 |accessdate=July 23, 2014 |work=Yahoo! Movies}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Teen Choice Award for Choice Movie Actor \u2013 Sci-Fi/Fantasy|Choice Movie Actor: Sci-Fi/Fantasy]]\n| [[Andrew Garfield]]\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[Teen Choice Award for Choice Movie Actress \u2013 Sci-Fi/Fantasy|Choice Movie Actress: Sci-Fi/Fantasy]]\n| [[Emma Stone]]\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[Teen Choice Award for Choice Movie Villain|Choice Movie: Villain]]\n| [[Jamie Foxx]]\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| Choice Movie: Liplock\n| Andrew Garfield and Emma Stone\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"5\"| [[2015 Kids' Choice Awards|Kids' Choice Awards]]\n| Favorite Movie\n| ''The Amazing Spider-Man 2''\n| {{nom}}\n| rowspan=\"5\" style=\"text-align:center;\"| <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mirror.co.uk/3am/celebrity-news/kids-choice-awards-winners-losers-5421141|title=Kids' Choice Awards: All the winners and losers at this year's gunge-fest|publisher=[[Daily Mirror]]|work=Simon Keegan|date=March 29, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/kids-choice-awards-complete-winners-783761|title=Kids' Choice Awards 2015: The Complete Winners List|work=The Hollywood Reporter|date=March 28, 2015}}</ref>\n|-\n| Favorite Movie Actor\n| Jamie Foxx\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| Favorite Movie Actress\n| Emma Stone\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| Favorite Male Action Star\n| Andrew Garfield\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| Favorite Villain\n| Jamie Foxx\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[41st Saturn Awards|Saturn Awards]]\n| Best Comic-to-Film Motion Picture\n| ''The Amazing Spider-Man 2''\n| {{nom}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| <ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.dreadcentral.com/news/91907/2015-saturn-awards-nominees-announced/ | title=2015 Saturn Awards Nominees Announced | publisher=[[Dread Central]] | work=DC Desk | date=March 3, 2015 | accessdate=April 5, 2016 | author=Barton, Steve}}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" |[[American Society of Composers, Authors and Publishers|ASCAP Awards]]\n| Top Box Office Films\n| ''The Amazing Spider-Man 2''\n| {{won}}\n| rowspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;\"| <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ascap.com/press/2015/0309-ascap-honors-top-film-and-television-music-composers.aspx|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160331125852/http://www.ascap.com/press/2015/0309-ascap-honors-top-film-and-television-music-composers.aspx|archivedate=March 31, 2016|title=ASCAP Honors Top Film & TV Composers at 30th Annual Awards|publisher=[[American Society of Composers, Authors and Publishers|ASCAP]]|date=March 10, 2015|accessdate=November 17, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ascap.com/eventsawards/awards/filmtv/2015/top-box-office-films.aspx|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160331125346/http://www.ascap.com/eventsawards/awards/filmtv/2015/top-box-office-films.aspx|archivedate=March 31, 2016|title=Top Box Office Films|publisher=[[American Society of Composers, Authors and Publishers|ASCAP]]|date=2015|accessdate=November 17, 2015}}</ref>\n|-\n| ASCAP Honors Top Film & TV Composers\n| [[Hans Zimmer]] and The Magnificent Six\n| {{won}}\n|-\n|}\n\n== Future ==\n\n=== Cancelled sequels and spin-offs ===\n{{quote box|\n| align = right\n| width = 30em\n| quote = It's a big day here at Sony. [[Kevin Feige|Kevin [Feige]]], [[Amy Pascal|Amy [Pascal]]] and their teams have done an incredible job. The Marvel process is very thorough, and that's why their results are so outstanding. I'm confident Spider-Man will be no exception. I've worked with a number of up-and-coming directors who have gone on to be superstars and believe that [[Jon Watts|Jon [Watts]]] is just such an outstanding talent. For Spidey himself, we saw many terrific young actors, but [[Tom Holland (actor)|Tom [Holland]]]'s screen tests were special.| source =&nbsp;\u2014[[Tom Rothman]], Chairman of [[Sony Pictures Motion Picture Group]]<ref name=tomnewspidey />}}\nSony had originally intended the film to launch an expansive film universe around Spider-Man to compete with the [[Marvel Cinematic Universe]]. In 2013, Sony announced a third ''Amazing Spider-Man'' film with a release date of June 10, 2016, which Alex Kurtzman, Roberto Orci, and Jeff Pinkner would return to write, and a fourth film with a release date of May 4, 2018.<ref name=\"The Hollywood Reporter\">{{cite web|url=http://hollywoodreporter.com/news/sony-sets-release-dates-third-569963|title=Sony Sets Release Dates for Third and Fourth 'Amazing Spider-Man' Films|work=The Hollywood Reporter|date=June 17, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/amazing-spider-man-3-bringing-640074|title=Sony Snags 'Amazing Spider-Man 2' Writers for Third Film (Exclusive)|last=Kit|first=Borys|work=The Hollywood Reporter|date=October 2, 2013|accessdate=October 2, 2013}}</ref> The series was to include spin-off films featuring the [[Sinister Six]] and [[Venom (Marvel Comics character)|Venom]], with [[Drew Goddard]] writing and directing ''Sinister Six'' and Kurtzman directing a ''Venom'' script co-written by himself, Orci, and [[Ed Solomon]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.deadline.com/2013/12/spider-man-spinoffs-sony-marc-webb-alex-kurtzman-roberto-orci-jeff-pinkner-ed-solomon-drew-goddard/|title=Sony Sets Spider-Man Spinoffs 'Venom,' 'Sinister Six' With New \"Franchise Brain Trust\"|last=Patten|first=Dominic|website=Deadline Hollywood|date=December 13, 2013|accessdate=December 14, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/x-men-amazing-spider-man-668376 |title=Forget Franchises: Why 2014 Will Be Hollywood's Year of the 'Shared Universe' |work=The Hollywood Reporter |date=January 6, 2014 |first=Borys |last=Kit |accessdate=April 12, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/spider-man-spin-sinister-six-694345|title=Spider-Man Spinoff 'Sinister Six' Names Director|work=The Hollywood Reporter |accessdate=April 7, 2014}}</ref> ''Sinister Six'' had been planned for a November 11, 2016 release.<ref name=\"Spidey 3 2018\" /><ref name=LisaJoyNolan>{{cite web|url=http://www.deadline.com/2014/08/female-superhero-movie-spider-man-sony/|title=Sony Launches Female Superhero Movie Mining Spider-Man Universe|last=Busch|first=Anita|website=Deadline Hollywood|date=August 4, 2014|accessdate=August 5, 2014 | archivedate= February 2, 2015| archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20150202013512/http://deadline.com/2014/08/female-superhero-movie-spider-man-sony-810253/| url-status=live}}</ref> Additionally, by August 2014, Sony had hired Lisa Joy Nolan to write the script for a 2017 film starring Felicia Hardy / Black Cat.<ref name=LisaJoyNolan /> Sony revealed plans for a spin-off based on ''[[Spider-Man 2099]]'' to be released in late 2017.<ref>{{Cite web |url= https://moviepilot.com/posts/2875570/ |title= Details for a Spider-Man 2099 movie Released? |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20161208044857/http://moviepilot.com/posts/2875570 |archive-date= Dec 8, 2016 |url-status= dead |access-date= October 15, 2019 }}</ref>\n\nHowever, between December 2013 and the release of ''The Amazing Spider-Man 2'' in May 2014, Garfield and Webb revealed that while they would both return for the third film, neither was certain of their involvement in the fourth, with Webb confirming that he would not be directing.<ref name=\"Budget-WebbASM3\">{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2014/film/news/analysts-sony-pictures-needs-to-release-more-release-more-tentpoles-1201118909/|title=Analysts: Sony Needs More Bigscreen Franchises|last=Cheney|first=Alexandra|work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] | date = February 25, 2014|accessdate=February 25, 2014 | archivedate= April 28, 2014 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20140428211458/http://variety.com/2014/film/news/analysts-sony-pictures-needs-to-release-more-release-more-tentpoles-1201118909/ | url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"DiLeo\">{{cite web|url=http://www.ign.com/articles/2013/12/10/andrew-garfield-may-not-be-in-the-amazing-spider-man-4|title=Andrew Garfield May Not Be in The Amazing Spider-Man 4|last=DiLeo|first=Adam|publisher=IGN|date=December 10, 2013|accessdate=December 14, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thedailybeast.com/articles/2014/03/15/marc-webb-takes-us-inside-the-amazing-spider-man-2-and-discusses-his-rise-to-the-a-list.html|title=Marc Webb Takes Us Inside 'The Amazing Spider-Man 2' and Discusses His Rise to the A-List|work=The Daily Beast|date=March 15, 2014|accessdate=March 15, 2014}}</ref> Following the mixed critical reviews and franchise-low box office performance of ''The Amazing Spider-Man 2'', the future of the franchise was unclear. By July 2014, Orci had left the third film to work on ''[[Star Trek Beyond]]'',<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.ign.com/articles/2014/07/11/roberto-orci-off-the-amazing-spider-man-franchise-no-clear-timeline-for-tasm-3-venom-or-sinister-six|title=Roberto Orci off the Amazing Spider-Man franchise, no clear timeline for TASM 3, Venom, or Sinister Six|publisher=IGN|date=July 11, 2014|accessdate=July 11, 2014}}</ref> ''The Amazing Spider-Man 3'', which would have included Chris Cooper returning as Norman Osborn<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=_VwzZMSy_k8|title=Marc Webb Confirms Mysterio And Kraven As Sinister Six !|publisher=[[YouTube]]|date=August 20, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.comicbookresources.com/article/amazing-spider-man-3-would-have-starred-norman-osborns-head-box | title=\"Amazing Spider-Man 3\" Would Have Starred Norman Osborn's Head In A Box | publisher=[[Comic Book Resources]] | date=March 21, 2016 | accessdate=July 26, 2016}}</ref> and focused on Peter recovering from Gwen's death,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://insidemovies.ew.com/2014/05/08/spider-man-marc-webb-gwen-stacy/|title='Amazing Spider-Man 2' director Marc Webb on Gwen Stacy's fate in sequel: 'There's a cost to being a hero'|last= Vilkomerson |first=Sara|work=Entertainment Weekly|date=May 8, 2014|accessdate=May 8, 2014}}</ref> was delayed to an unspecified date in 2018, and ''The Amazing Spider-Man 4'' was moved to a later, unknown date.<ref name=\"Spidey 3 2018\">{{cite web|last=McNary|first=Drew|title=Sony Pushes Back 'Spider-Man 3' to 2018, Dates 'Sinister Six' for 2016|url=https://variety.com/2014/film/news/spider-man-spinoff-sinister-six-dated-for-nov-11-2016-amazing-spider-man-3-back-to-2018-1201267269|work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|date=July 23, 2014|accessdate=July 23, 2014}}</ref>\n\nFollowing the 2014 [[Sony Pictures hack]], Sony was revealed to have been in talks to have [[Sam Raimi]] return to the franchise to direct a new trilogy for the character and was in discussion with [[Marvel Studios]] about including Spider-Man in the [[Marvel Cinematic Universe]] film ''[[Captain America: Civil War]]''. Marvel reportedly was unhappy with some of the terms of the proposed arrangement, including the film rights staying with Sony, and both talks allegedly ceased.<ref name=\"Ben Fritz\">{{cite web|last1=Fritz|first1=Ben|title=Sony, Marvel Discussed Spider-Man Movie Crossover|url=https://blogs.wsj.com/speakeasy/2014/12/09/sony-marvel-discussed-spider-man-movie-crossover/|work=Wall Street Journal|accessdate=December 9, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.slashfilm.com/spider-man-animated-comedy-marvel-crossover/|title=Sony Leak Reveals Studio Considering Lord/Miller Spider-Man Comedy, Marvel Crossover|last=Han|first=Angie|publisher=/Film|date=December 9, 2014}}</ref> In early 2015, a deal between the studios that allows Spider-Man to be in the Marvel Cinematic Universe was reached, effectively cancelling ''The Amazing Spider-Man'' franchise.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://variety.com/2015/film/news/details-spider-man-appear-in-sony-and-marvel-movies-1201429039/ | title=Spider-Man: How Sony, Marvel Will Benefit from Unique Deal (Exclusive) | work=Variety | date=February 10, 2015 | accessdate=June 24, 2015}}</ref>\n\n=== Marvel Cinematic Universe ===\n{{Main|Spider-Man: Homecoming|Spider-Man: Far From Home}}\n\nIn February 2015, Sony and Marvel Studios announced that a new iteration of Spider-Man would appear in the Marvel Cinematic Universe, with the character appearing in ''[[Captain America: Civil War]]''.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.ign.com/articles/2015/02/10/sinister-six-delayed-at-sony-spider-man-to-appear-in-captain-america-civil-war | title=Sinister Six Delayed at Sony, Spider-Man to Appear in ''Captain America: Civil War'' | publisher=IGN.com | date=February 10, 2015 | accessdate=February 10, 2015}}</ref> Sony Pictures will continue to finance, distribute, own and have final creative control of the ''Spider-Man'' films. Marvel Studios and Sony will explore opportunities to integrate other characters of the MCU into future ''Spider-Man'' films.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://marvel.com/news/movies/24062/sony_pictures_entertainment_brings_marvel_studios_into_the_amazing_world_of_spider-man | title=Sony Pictures Entertainment Brings Marvel Studios Into The Amazing World Of Spider-Man | publisher=Marvel | date=February 9, 2015 | accessdate=February 10, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://masterherald.com/marvel-studios-confirms-cancellation-of-amazing-spider-man-3-as-pre-production-work-begins-for-spider-man-reboot/17621/|title=Marvel Studios Confirms Cancellation of 'Amazing Spider-Man 3' as Pre-Production Work Begins for 'Spider-Man' Reboot|publisher=Master Herald|work=Kazem Sedighzadeh|date=May 28, 2015|accessdate=November 17, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.christianpost.com/news/amazing-spider-man-3-cancelled-as-spider-man-joins-the-marvel-universe-134293/|title='Amazing Spider-Man 3' Release Date Cancelled as Spider-Man Joins Marvel Movies|publisher=[[The Christian Post]]|work=Liezl Dunuan|date=February 20, 2015|accessdate=November 17, 2015}}</ref> Sony released a standalone film titled ''[[Spider-Man: Homecoming]]'', produced by [[Kevin Feige]] and [[Amy Pascal]], on July 7, 2017, with [[Tom Holland (actor)|Tom Holland]] starring as the new Spider-Man.<ref name=tomnewspidey>{{cite web | url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/spider-man-finds-tom-holland-794761 | title='Spider-Man' Finds Tom Holland to Star as New Web-Slinger | work=The Hollywood Reporter | date=June 23, 2015 | accessdate=June 24, 2015}}</ref> Holland reprises his portrayal of the character in ''[[Avengers: Infinity War]]'', ''[[Avengers: Endgame]]'',<ref name=\"Atlanta\">{{cite web|url=http://collider.com/captain-america-civil-war-avengers-3-infinity-war-updates-russo-brothers/|title='Captain America: Civil War' Directors on Landing Spider-Man, 'Infinity War' Shooting Schedule|last=Cabin|first=Chris|publisher=[[Collider (website)|Collider]]|date=January 14, 2016|accessdate=January 14, 2016|archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6eXBPJg81?url=http://collider.com/captain-america-civil-war-avengers-3-infinity-war-updates-russo-brothers/|archivedate=January 14, 2016|url-status=live}}</ref> and ''[[Spider-Man: Far From Home]]''.<ref name=\"THRSP\">{{cite news |last1=Ford |first1=Rebecca |last2=Kit |first2=Borys |title='Spider-Man: Homecoming' Director in Talks to Return for Sequel |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/spider-man-homecoming-sequel-director-jon-watts-talks-return-1021942 |accessdate=September 8, 2018 |work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |date=July 19, 2017}}</ref>\n\nMarvel and Sony canceled their deal on 20 August 2019 over production issues and [[Spider-Man]] came back to Sony as a separate character, no longer part of the MCU.\nIn September 2019, Disney and Sony announced that a new deal had been reached, which includes a third Spider-Man film as well as one other film, both set in the MCU.<ref name=\"DisneySonySpidey3\">{{Cite web |url=https://variety.com/2019/film/news/sony-marvel-tom-holland-spider-man-1203351489/ |title=Sony, Marvel Make Up: Companies Will Produce Third 'Spider-Man' Film |last=Lang |first=Brent |work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] |date=September 27, 2019 |access-date=September 27, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190927160452/https://variety.com/2019/film/news/sony-marvel-tom-holland-spider-man-1203351489/ |archive-date=September 27, 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n=== Sony's Marvel Universe ===\n{{Main|Sony's Marvel Universe}}\n\nBy March 2016, Sony was moving forward with the standalone ''Venom'' film with Dante Harper writing the script, [[Avi Arad]] and Matt Tolmach producing and [[Tom Hardy]] as the titular character.<ref>{{cite web | url= http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/spider-man-spinoff-venom-revived-872844 | title='Spider-Man' Spinoff 'Venom' Revived at Sony (Exclusive) | work= [[The Hollywood Reporter]] | date= March 4, 2016 | accessdate=March 4, 2016 | last= Kit | first= Borys }}</ref> [[Venom (2018 film)|The film]] was eventually released in 2018 and was directed by [[Ruben Fleischer]].\n\nAfter the film's unexpected box office success, Sony began development for [[Venom 2|a second ''Venom'' film]]<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://variety.com/2019/film/news/venom-sequel-sony-tom-hardy-1203098558/ |title = 'Venom' Sequel in Works with Kelly Marcel Returning to Pen Script (EXCLUSIVE)|date = January 7, 2019}}</ref> and also announced a ''[[Morbius (film)|Morbius]]'' film<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/spider-man-spinoff-morbius-living-vampire-movie-works-power-rangers-writers-1056702|title='Spider-Man' Spinoff: Morbius the Living Vampire Movie in the Works With 'Power Rangers' Writers|website=The Hollywood Reporter}}</ref> to be released in 2020,<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://deadline.com/2019/01/morbius-ghostbusters-movie-release-dates-2020-1202542336/ |title = 'Morbius' & 'Ghostbusters' Solidify Summer 2020 Release Dates|date = January 26, 2019}}</ref> with [[Daniel Espinosa]] directing the film and [[Jared Leto]] starring as the title character.<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://variety.com/2018/film/news/jared-leto-spider-man-spinoff-morbius-1202799820/ | title=Jared Leto to Star in 'Spider-Man' Spinoff 'Morbius' from Director Daniel Espinosa| date=June 27, 2018}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of films featuring powered exoskeletons]]\n\n==Footnotes==\n{{notelist}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== Further reading ==\n{{Refbegin}}\n* {{cite book|last=Marvel|first=Press|title=The Amazing Spider-Man 2: The Oscorp Files: A Marvel Storybook with Audio|url=https://books.google.com/?id=rOceAwAAQBAJ&dq=amazing+spiderman+2|publisher=[[Disney Publishing Worldwide]]|isbn=978-1-4847-0163-8|ref=harv1|date=2014-04-01}}\n* {{cite book|last=Stan Lee|first=Gerry Conway|title=The Amazing Spider-Man: The Death of Gwen Stacy|url=https://archive.org/details/stanleepresentsa00lees_0|url-access=registration|quote=amazing spiderman 2.|publisher=[[Marvel Comics]] (2002)|isbn=978-0-7851-1026-2|ref=harv1|year=2002}}\n*{{cite book|last=Barbara Brownie|first=Danny Graydon|title=The Superhero Costume: Identity and Disguise in Fact and Fiction|url=https://books.google.com/?id=QOAkCgAAQBAJ&pg=PT190&dq=amazing+spiderman+2#v=onepage&q=a